title: mr. lynch's pudding pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Set aside in the fridge.
Grind up graham crackers until its fine and powdery.
Add apple juice until it forms a paste.
Place into a pie pan and distribute evenly throughout.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour in pudding.
Enjoy!

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add sauce, soup, milk and chilies.
Place alternately in casserole with taco flavored chips.
Start with chips; top with 1/2 to 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream and pour into greased and floured loaf pans (3).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Make buttered toast.
Sprinkle mixture over buttered toast.
Return toast to broiler.
Serve hot.

title: cashew nut patties
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add cubed bread (brown).
Add to rest of ingredients, make into patties and fry in oil.

title: sean's favorite banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Eagle Brand milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Layer bowl with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers until all is gone. Refrigerate.

title: the underwood special black-eyed pea and corn salad
directions: Combine peas, corn, celery, red bell pepper and green onions in a large bowl.
Shake oil, vinegar, honey, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a tightly covered container until well blended.
Pour dressing over the vegetables and toss well.
Serve on lettuce. Yields 4 servings.

title: big mama's pralines
directions: Make a syrup with 3 1/2 cups of sugar, salt and milk.
While this is coming to a boil, put the 1/2 cup remaining sugar in a pan until it is light in color.
Add syrup mixture to browned sugar while stirring, but stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat when forms a ball in cold water.
Beat until creamy; add nuts and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: ice strawberries
directions: Blend in blender.
Garnish with strawberry and orange slice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and egg together.
Add to squash.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle with cheese, cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: zucchini lemon bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil and lemon juice. Beat by hand until well blended; add zucchini.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into zucchini mixture. Fold in nuts.
Bake in cookie sheet at 350°.
Frost with Lemon Frosting.

title: pineapple mint sauce
directions: Cook until thick.
Add green food coloring and one teaspoon of essence of peppermint.
Chill.

title: mushroom-barley soup
directions: Cook barley in 1 1/2 cups beef stock in soup kettle until tender. Add remaining stock, tamari and sherry. Saute onion and garlic in butter until softened. Add mushrooms and salt. Cook until tender.
Add vegetables and liquid to barley. Season with pepper to taste. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes on low heat.

title: cheese cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Pour into crust and bake at 375° for 20-30 minutes; cool completely.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla together; pour over cooled cake.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, cook beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat until beef is no longer pink, drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes; remove from heat, stir in milk, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese and rotini.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!!!!!

title: crispy ginger snaps
directions: Mix shortening and sugar, then add egg and molasses.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Using hands roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip top in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Leave space between each for spreading.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, cooked noodles and other ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Cook at 350° until fluffy. Makes a large amount, so it can be frozen.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Put first 5 ingredients together and heat in saucepan.
Mix peanuts and pretzels (broken into small pieces).
Mix with the Cheerios and Rice Chex.
Combine the ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Stir in the melted butter well.
Bake in oven at 225°.
Cover for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes longer without lid.
Cool.
Pour into containers and store.

title: lemon butter for meats
directions: Blend well.
Serve on hot steaks, chops or fish.
An additional garnish of lemon quarters provide more tartness, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure, add salt; sift again.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks beaten until thick and lemon colored (unbeaten if electric mixer is used).
Beat thoroughly.
Add brandy.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold into egg yolk mixture.
Gradually fold in dry ingredients, sprinkling about 1/4 cup at a time over the surface.
Beat until smooth (2 minutes with beater at medium speed).
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add remaining.
Bake in muffin pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
Batter will keep 5 to 6 weeks in refrigerator; just use it as you need it.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix apricot jam with egg yolks.
Divide the dough; put 1/2 on cookie sheet.
Press down evenly.
Spread jam mix on dough.
Roll out and cut the rest of the dough into strips.
Lay strips over jam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's lazy day salad
directions: Mix all together.
Fold in 1 medium container of Cool Whip. (Use dry pudding.)
Cool for at least two hours before serving.

title: favorite chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chickens; debone and save broth. Boil chopped onions in a separate boiler and save to pour over cornbread.
Mix corn meal and eggs with enough milk to make batter medium to rather thin. Heat enough oil to cover bottom of skillet and pour some of hot oil in batter.
Then pour batter into skillet and bake at 425° until done.
May brown under broiler if needed.
When cool, crumble cornbread in large roaster pan and pour cooked onions and water over it.
Keep adding chicken broth, salt and lots of pepper until desired taste and thickness.
Place bits of deboned chicken around in the dressing.
Bake in oven at 425° until rather firm.

title: snowball cake
directions: Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup water.
Stir and add the boiling water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and pineapple; stir.
Set in refrigerator until partially congealed.
Add 2/3 of the Cool Whip to pineapple mixture.
Stir.
Break 1/2 the angel food cake into pieces and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover cake with 1/2 of the gelatin, pineapple mixture.
Repeat the above with another layer of cake and pineapple.
Ice over the top with the remaining 1/3 of Cool
Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Let set overnight. Cut in small cubes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Mix onion, celery, rice, carrots and soyameat together and put into casserole.
Put oil, vegex, water, broth and soup into saucepan and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over casserole and mix gently.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: double chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add oil, zucchini, vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Sift dry ingredients together; then add chocolate chips.
Add to wet ingredients.
Blend well.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Salt and pepper chicken; add garlic salt, if desired.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 large can Parmesan cheese over chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve gravy left in baking dish over noodles.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water until tender.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour, Accent and salt.
Chop broccoli into small pieces and add to egg mixture.
Add Swiss cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour over top of crackers. Bake at 300° about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cook with aluminum foil over top, loosely covered.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour into a greased pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and blend with blender.
Slice apples and sprinkle with orange or lemon juice.
Dip the apples and enjoy.

title: potato curry
directions: Cut potatoes into halves; boil them for 15 minutes, or pressure cook (do not overcook).
Remove skin from potatoes.
Cut into small (1/3-inch) pieces.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Put mustard seed and urad dhal in oil.
Fry urad dhal until brown (30 seconds).
Brown cut onions.
Add green peppers, tomatoes and potatoes.
Add turmeric powder and salt to taste.
Stir entire ingredients; simmer for 2 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: caddo relish
directions: Heat very hot, but do not boil.
Can immediately.
Makes 9 pints.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray rack of roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut chicken into serving pieces and remove skin and excess fat.

title: mom's oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and black pepper. Roll chicken pieces to coat. Brown in a pan of melted butter and shortening. Place browned chicken pieces in a baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients into a large pot and bring to a boil. Pour over chicken pieces. Bake at 400° for about an hour.

title: seafood cocktail dip
directions: In medium bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or with assorted crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain off fat.
Put in a large kettle and add the beans.
Mix catsup, white and brown sugar, garlic salt and vinegar.
Mix well and add to beans; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or can be put into crock-pot.

title: tomato gravy for pasta dishes
directions: Heat oil slightly in a heavy, large roaster.
Add onions and garlic and saute on low heat until transparent.
Add more oil, if necessary.
Be careful not to use too much or sauce will be oily. Slowly add tomato paste, blending and frying, until all is added and is darker in color, about 1 hour.
Add whole tomatoes and liquid; stir well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar (more if you want sweeter sauce).
Add salt and red pepper to taste.
Add more seasoning after cooking several hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake biscuits, a few at a time, in bag.

title: fruited rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter.
Stir in rice, raisins, chicken broth and basil.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: knox blox
directions: In medium bowl, combine Knox unflavored gelatine and fruit-flavored gelatine; add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 6 dozen blox.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dust tablespoon of Jell-O on top. Chill thoroughly.
Served on lettuce.

title: strawberry jubilee
directions: Break half cake in bite size pieces.
Put in the bottom of a large bowl.
Mix Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Slice strawberries.
Put in refrigerator while making pudding mix.
Pour Jell-O mix (half of it) over the cake.
Repeat the same procedure for another layer.
Put pudding mix over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator until congealed.
Sprinkle top with pecans.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a paper bag.
Mix egg and milk in bowl.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Shake in flour mixture.
Place in baking pan with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375 degrees, turning once.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Boil ingredients for exactly 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and cool.
Serve over ice cream with almonds or pecans.

title: lunch box tortilla roll-up
directions: Spread tortilla with refried beans.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Chill. Roll items into balls and bake 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool and shake in powdered sugar.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add
milk, egg whites, honey (or molasses), oil and other ingredients.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moist. Fill
muffin cups almost full.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pecans and coconut; sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Pour prepared cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together. Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: linguine alla carbonara
directions: Let eggs, cream and butter stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
In skillet, cook bacon until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Beat together eggs and cream just until blended. Toss hot pasta with butter.
Pour egg mixture over and toss until pasta is well coated.
Add bacon, cheese and parsley.
Toss to mix. Season to taste with pepper.
Serve at once.
Serves 4. The heat from the pasta cooks the eggs.

title: one-step skillet supper
directions: In large skillet, combine ground meat mix, vegetable juice, uncooked macaroni, green peppers and garlic powder.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When macaroni is tender, remove lid from skillet and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, over heat for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Best if served immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage rice skillet meal
directions: Crumble 1 to 1 1/2 pounds pork sausage into skillet and brown. Pour off some of the fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for about 1 hour or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
You may add a bit more broth or water, if needed.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Wash vegetables; put through the coarse blade of a food chopper or chop well.
Place in a large container, add salt and let stand overnight.
The next morning, drain vegetables.
Tie pickling spice in a bag.
Combine sugar and vinegar and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add spice bag and all remaining ingredients with sugar/vinegar mixture and simmer until well seasoned.
Remove spice bag, pack vegetables while hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: czech bread dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Add bread cubes last.) Divide into 3 dumplings.
Boil 20 minutes. Cut in 1/2 when taken out to let steam out.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, add together sugar, salt and soda.
Warm buttermilk by heating, but not boiling.
Cool to warm.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add yeast.
This mixture will foam so beat in 3 cups flour, eggs, and oil until smooth.
Add 4 or more cups of flour, one at a time, until you have a batter you can pick up with your hands.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add others and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wyoming whopper cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Mix until almost smooth.
Add oats, soda, raisins and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Will be sticky.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fred's whole wheat honey bread
directions: In mixing bowl stir whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine beaten egg, buttermilk, honey and melted margarine.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: donna's zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir dry ingredients, zucchini, nuts and raisins
together.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.
Double recipe and it will make 3 nice size loaves.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Using an electric mixer or food processor, beat braunschweiger, chili sauce, horseradish and hot pepper sauce until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate until mixture firms up, approx. 1 hour.
In a medium bowl, mash cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth and spreadable.
Turn liverwurst mixture out onto a sheet of foil and mold it into a ball.
Using a small spatula, frost with cream cheese mixture.
Decorate with sliced stuffed green olives.

title: truffle cheesecake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add butter.
Press into spring-form pan.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Bake cake with no oil and use milk instead of water; let cool. Have strawberries defrosted and ready to go.
Mix Cool Whip with strawberries and blend well with electric mixer.
Frost cake and refrigerate before you serve.
Enough to do 1 (9 x 13) pan or 1 round 2-layer cake.
You can also use bananas (banana cake mix or yellow) or pineapple (pineapple cake mix, drained well).

title: pie meringue(large recipe)
directions: Mix egg whites and salt; whip past frothy stage, approximately 1 1/2 minutes (high speed).
Add sugar gradually while beating. Beat until the sugar has dissolved.
The meringue should be stiff enough to hold peaks but not dry.
Spread on pie to edge of crust. Bake approximately 12 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
Meringue for 8 (8-inch) pies.

title: frozen peach dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for garnish.
Pat remaining crumbs on bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: greek macaroni squares(pastitsio)
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onions in butter until golden; add meat until browned.
Add tomato sauce, cinnamon, salt and garlic; cover and simmer 1/2 hour or until thickened.
Cook macaroni in salted water until barely tender (about 12 minutes); drain and rinse under cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate layers of macaroni, meat sauce and cheese. Dust with cinnamon.
Pour custard sauce over macaroni.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on until cooked.
Place in cold water. Remove skins.
When cool enough, slice into 1/4-inch thickness and place in serving dish.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Serves 6.

title: scooter's favorite steak
directions: Roll steak in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry quickly, turning once.
Add other ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: sinful salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine gelatin and boiling water.
Stir with a rubber spatula until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Let mixture cool and add bananas, pecans, strawberries, pineapple. Mix thoroughly and divide in half.
Pour one half of the gelatin mixture into a 12 x 8 inch pan and refrigerate until mixture is set (about 1 hour).
Keep the remaining gelatin at room temperature.
Spread sour cream evenly over set gelatin.
Cover sour cream with remaining gelatin mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until firmly set (about 1 1/2 hours or overnight).

title: mabel's banana bread
directions: Mix the bananas with the soda and set aside. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the eggs.
Fold in the flour. Add the mashed banana mixture.*
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° or until pie is firm (cooking time about 45 minutes).

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients; set aside.
Brush chicken with skim milk, coat with cereal mixture, and place on nonstick baking pan.
Dot cutlet with margarine.

title: pastry for 2-crust pie
directions: Cut flour and shortening together to form small size peas. Sprinkle in water 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing with a fork until all flour is moistened.
Make into a crust.

title: bean soup
directions: Saute ground beef.
Add all ingredients in a slow cooker. Simmer for 45 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Can substitute any beans for the above with the exception of the chili beans.

title: sarah's white bread
directions: May be used as pizza crust.
Makes 3 large pizzas.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice onion and cucumbers.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Leftover dressing may be re-used.
Chill.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Clean shrimp, cook in margarine and add onion.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add cream of mushroom soup and curry powder. When mixture comes to a boil, turn off heat.

title: low calorie pickled green bean salad
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions, drain and cool.
Combine green beans and relish.
Chill and serve.

title: california wheat open-faced squares
directions: Wash and thinly slice tomatoes.
Open and slice the wheat rolls or bread in half and place them on the top of a broiler or jelly roll pan.
Place one slice of cheese on the top of each roll half. Place one slice of tomato on top of the cheese and salt and pepper each slice of tomato lightly.
Place one slice of precooked bacon on top of the tomato slice.

Place the open-faced sandwiches on the top shelf of the oven and set both dials on the stovetop to broil. (To broil, place the pan on the very top shelf of the oven, set the two stovetop dials on broil, and be sure to leave the door cracked open when broiling.)
Broil the sandwiches until the bacon is crisp and the cheese is melted.
Place the half sandwiches on a serving plate on the serving table.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper until onion is transparent. Drain and set aside.
In a large pan, such as a Dutch oven, melt cheese, taco sauce and tomato sauce, stirring until smooth.
Add beef mixture.
One can keep this warm by putting it in a crock-pot on low heat.
Serve with tortilla chips, Doritos, etc.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Place cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread pineapple over cherry pie filling. Crumble cake mix over cherries and pineapple. Pour melted butter over mixture then top with coconut. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-sour chicken or pork
directions: Combine brown sugar and cornstarch; stir in vinegar, pineapple juice, green pepper, soy sauce, pimento, garlic powder and ginger. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Serve over chicken, pork or spareribs.

title: broccoli almondine
directions: Cook broccoli per directions on package; drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli, soup, cheese, mushrooms, bread crumbs and almonds.
Save some almonds to sprinkle on top.
Turn mixture into casserole and bake in 300° oven until bubbly.

title: david's sauteed rockfish
directions: Preheat electric skillet or frying pan to medium heat.
Melt margarine, add garlic and spices and saute for 5 minutes.
Add fish.
Increase heat to medium-high and cook until halfway done. Add vermouth.
Turn fish.
Continue cooking until done.
Stir in parsley and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Sieve apricots; add reserved syrup, if necessary, to make 1 cup.
Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with apricot mixture.
Stir in walnuts; turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 50 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: rose's curry chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Stir in soup, beer, curry powder, oregano, pepper and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Put chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then uncover for another 25 minutes, basting it.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top for 5 more minutes until melted.
Serve with rice.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Adjust oven rack to lower third position and preheat oven to 350°F (170°C).
Generously butter 9 x 5 x 3-inch (23 x 13 x 8cm) loaf pan.
(Larger pan will yield flat, wide loaf; smaller pan will produce narrow, tall loaf.)
Insert metal blade and put flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and apricots into work bowl. Pulse 6 to 8 times, in pulses lasting 1 second each, just until apricots are very coarsely chopped.
Remove and set aside.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients to make a sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan. Cream the butter and sugar together.

Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour with salt and baking powder (if you use self-rising flour, leave out the salt and baking powder) in separate bowl. Beat in with an electric mixer, 1/3 of the flour mixture, the 1/3 of the milk.
Do this until all the flour and milk are used. Add vanilla and lemon juice. Beat until creamy.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Cool before turning out of pan.

title: chocolate topping for ice cream
directions: Add cocoa to powdered sugar and salt.
Mix in milk and butter. Cook over low heat until thick.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute sliced onions in butter in a Dutch oven pot. When onions are golden and soft, add 4 cups boiling water.
Add garlic powder, beef bouillon cubes and soy sauce. Simmer 45 minutes.

title: green chili bites
directions: Slightly beat egg and pour onto greased 13 x 9 cookie sheet. Top with grated cheeses. Add chopped green chilies and jalapeno peppers. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Over low heat combine first six ingredients until melted and blended together.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour (you may need to use higher heat according to each person's oven).
Mix each pie in separate bowl when preparing more than one pie.

title: spanish sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, green peppers and red peppers and put in kettle; add mustard, turmeric, salt, sugar and 1 quart vinegar.
Boil together flour mixed with 1 pint vinegar. Stir until creamy and add to first mixture and boil 5 minutes longer.
Put in jars and seal with rings and bands or seal with paraffin.
Makes 10 pints.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots with oil, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and allspice; mix.
Then add flour and salt slowly; mix thoroughly.
Add baking soda and walnuts to mixture.
Then put into a 13 x 9 or 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is firm.

title: cheese grits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown meat lightly in olive or vegetable oil.
Saute onions and bell peppers until somewhat translucent.
Combine meat, onions, peppers and other ingredients, reserving wine and mushrooms until last.
Cook slowly several hours, adjusting seasonings to taste.
Yields 30 cups.

title: swedish kiss pudding
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put in preheated 450° oven.
Turn oven off.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Rinse blueberries from mix with cold water and drain. Combine contents of topping packet from mix with almonds.

title: salmon with saffron and caviar cream
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, add oil and saute shallots until soft (do not brown).
Add broth, lime juice and vinegars.
Heat to a mild boil and add cream, saffron and caviar. Mix well and place salmon in pan.
Cover and reduce heat slightly and simmer until salmon is moderately firm.
Remove and keep warm. Reduce sauce over medium heat until creamy.
Serve over salmon. Serves 2.

title: quick and easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Separate bread sticks, but leave coiled. Brush each bread stick with margarine. Combine sugar and cinnamon on a plate. Dip bread sticks in cinnamon mixture. Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: just right slaw
directions: Arrange cabbage, onions and pepper in large serving bowl. Sprinkle the 2 teaspoons of sugar on top.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep several days.

title: tomato hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook down on low, but still boiling, until all vegetables are tender, about 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Makes 4 pints.

title: egg nog cakes
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1-inch pieces and set aside.
Melt butter; mix with confectioners sugar until smooth.
Add Jack Daniel's whiskey to dipping consistency (set aside what is not used; you will have to add the Jack Daniel's whiskey as you go along to keep dipping consistency).
Mix pecans and vanilla wafers in a large bowl; set aside.

title: hot shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Combine in bowl all ingredients except eggs.
Mix.
Pour into casserole.
Garnish with eggs. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Place spinach in salad bowl.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp; spoon bacon and drippings over spinach.
Combine light cream, eggs, vinegar, sugar, salt, paprika and pepper.
Pour into skillet; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Pour over spinach; toss until leaves are well coated.
Garnish with egg wedges, if desired.
Serve at room temperature, warm.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and milk; mix well.
Add flour until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Stir in sliced apples.
Heat shortening in frypan until hot.
Pour or spoon pancake-size portions into frypan and fry both sides until golden brown. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chinese upside-down casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add chopped onion, celery and sliced water chestnuts.
Stir and cook until crisp and tender.
Add onion soup mix and pepper. Stir and add mushroom soup. Remove from skillet and put in casserole dish.
Top with Chinese noodles. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
6 to 8 servings.
Soy sauce may be added if desired.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add 2 cups mayonnaise.
Mix and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend first four ingredients.
Beat egg and vanilla together. Add to first mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill the dough.
Form small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with glass dipped in sugar or flatten and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aristocrat pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Make cool brine of water and salt. Pour over cucumbers and let stand 1 week.
Stir every morning. Drain pickles and cover with cold water (just to cover) mixed with alum.
Simmer 10 minutes, then drain.

title: ice cream(easy to make)
directions: Chill the milk overnight.
Whip the chilled milk.
Add the Cool Whip.
Add sugar to fruit (sweeten to taste).
Fold into whipped mixture.
Place in freezer.
Before the mixture completely freezes, stir it well.
Remove from freezer at least one hour before serving.
Best when it is a little soft.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients except muffin mix.
Mix well, then add corn muffin mix.
Pour into well-greased, hot pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into large mixing bowl.
Add ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard and honey; mix well.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, onion, garlic and liquid smoke.
Stir in ground beef last.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes on 350° or until bacon is browned.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut in quarters lengthwise and in half crosswise.
Can use baby carrots.
Bring water and salt to a boil; add carrots.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to carrots.
Gently stir over low heat until butter is melted and carrots are glazed.

title: butter dips
directions: Put butter in 400° oven until melted. Combine rest of ingredients. Stir just until dough forms. Knead dough. Roll into 8-inch square. Cut square in half, then cut each half into nine 4-inch strips. Dip each strip into melted butter, coating both sides; arrange strips close together in pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 18 sticks.

title: tangy lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and water in a small saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and butter; cook until thoroughly melted.
Serve sauce warm over cake, fruit or ice cream.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix liquid ingredients.
Add dry and liquid ingredients together until liquid coats flour.
Do not overmix.
Pour in 9 x 5-inch greased pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Add the sugar gradually.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture.
Scald the milk to which has been added the butter.
Add hot milk last.
Bake for 1/2 half at 350°.

title: good meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place in baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then throw in potatoes and put it in a greased casserole dish. Crumple Ritz crackers on top. Cook at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fry in frying pan with butter flavored Crisco.
Spoon batter like pancakes.

title: jewish noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with brown sugar and pecan halves on top.
Dot with butter.
Mix drained noodles with sour cream and cream cheese, a little more butter and 2 beaten eggs. Add pineapple and spread on brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Remove onions and brown steak.
Add salt and 1 tablespoon of chili powder as steak browns.
Cook rice as directed on package.
When 2/3 done, add onions, steak and pimentos (chopped).
Bake slowly 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: snow log
directions: Soften cream cheese, then beat until smooth. Work in the rest of the ingredients but be sure to blot all the moisture from the cherries with paper towels. You may have to add more confectioners sugar. You can safely add as much as you can work in. Shape into a log 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter. Roll in wafer crumbs to coat. Store in waxed paper in a plastic bag. Keep in refrigerator. Slice in thin slices to serve.

title: ice tea
directions: Brew 7 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cold water.

title: my mother's rice pudding
directions: Stir all together and put in shallow pan or baking dish and cook until thick and a light brown. Cover with marshmallows and bake until brown. Watch closely so it doesn't burn.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and add cheese.
Beat eggs and add soup and mayonnaise.
Stir in onion. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted bread crumbs.

title: cheese squares
directions: Spread 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Spread the other package of crescent rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle nuts and 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Cut into squares after baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: delicious oatmeal bread
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oats and let stand 30 minutes. Add the molasses and soft butter. Dissolve the yeast in the warm water and add to the oat mixture.

title: zesty italian mini-breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Unroll breadsticks; do not separate.
Cut dough crosswise into five equal parts; separate into individual pieces.
In plastic bag, combine Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; add dough pieces.
Close bag and shake to coat; remove and
place on cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet with mini breadsticks on upper oven rack.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 14 minutes or until mini breadsticks are golden brown; remove.
Dip breadsticks in warm sauce.

title: jaeger potatoes(austrian mountain dish)
directions: Boil
potatoes whole with skins on.
While potatoes are cooking,
brown
bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon bits
from	skillet.
In
bacon fat, brown onions until almost black.
Drain
off	fat.
Peel and coarsely chop hot potatoes. Add bacon
bits,
onions
and	butter to potatoes.
Mix well. Serve as a side dish with meat and gravy.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine and beat until fluffy.
Still using the electric mixer, add the vanilla and eggs.
Add cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Add the flour gradually.
In a separate bowl, add 2 tablespoons of sugar and the cinnamon.
Shape dough into 1-inch size balls; roll balls into sugar and cinnamon.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake cookies 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove carefully from the cookie sheets.
Place on cooling rack.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: jello-yogurt dessert
directions: Fix Jell-O and let set for 1 hour.
Whip the yogurt into Jell-O and let set.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey in a large pan sprayed with Pam until broken apart and browned.
Drain off any fat.
Add the green pepper and onion.
Reduce the heat and cover.
Cook over medium heat until peppers are tender.
Add the beans, tomatoes and chili mix. Simmer for 10 minutes and serve.
This freezes beautifully.
Store in individual serving sized containers.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown chickening skillet with onions. In a large bowl, mix all other ingredients together. Add chicken and place in 15 x 13 baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: monique's famous chili
directions: In one pan cook your ground meat.
When halfway done, add your onion and sausage until meat is done; drain.
In another pot add your tomato sauce, chili seasoning, chili with beans, water and stewed tomatoes.
When meat mixture is done, add to mixture.
Cook about 20 minutes on medium heat.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Parboil dry beans until soft.
Drain well.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot in order.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or 5 to 6 hours on high.
When using canned beans, drain liquid.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring butter and water to a boil. Remove from the heat; stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, almond extract, salt and baking soda until smooth. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake is golden brown and tests done. Cool for 20 minutes.

title: peruvian salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in prunes (pitted and undrained), pineapple (undrained) and chopped pecans. Refrigerate. The Bishop's Cafeterias, Iowa.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add 1/2 can onion rings. Top with the remaining 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain the vegetables.

title: creole sauce with ziti
directions: Saute onions in oil until
soft; do not brown.
Add bay leaf, tomatoes, pepper, cloves and sugar.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes; stir flour and water.
Remove bay leaf and cloves and cook
5 minutes more.
Pour
over
cooked
Ziti.
Serve
with grated cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: the best vegetable soup
directions: Wash, cut and boil together, all but macaroni and beans, for 30 minutes.
Then add last 2 ingredients and cook 10 minutes. Garnish with sour cream on top.
Serves 8.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Salt each piece.
Let stand stacked 1 hour in salt water. Rinse in cold water.
Cut in small pieces.
Cover with boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes; drain.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with chopped raw vegetables.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream and beat thoroughly the pulp, sugar and eggs.
Mix in sifted ingredients.
Add oil.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan for 45 to 50 minutes or until tests done.

title: chicken stew
directions: In large soup pot, boil chicken until done; slice vegetables. Take chicken out of broth and set aside to cool.
Pour out about 1/4 of the broth, then add sliced vegetables and soup to broth. Then take meat off chicken and add to soup.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a bowl, mix soup, milk, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake until heated through in a 350° oven, uncovered.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more, until onions are golden.
Serves 6.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a bowl and set aside.
Boil margarine, cocoa and water together and pour over sugar and flour while hot and mix.
Then beat in eggs and add baking soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat in buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 15 x 1-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: mandarin oranges with ginger
directions: In a bowl, combine mandarins and ginger, mix well. Refrigerate 30 minutes or longer.
Serve chilled as a dessert or pork or poultry side dish.
Serves 2.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls onto pizza pan, pressing down on perforations to seal.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, minced green onion and dill weed and spread on cooled crust.
Chop vegetables and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Suggested vegetables:
(chopped) broccoli flowerets, cauliflower, green peppers, tomato, black olives, green onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except gelatin. Stir gelatin in last. Chill about 2 hours. Can be fixed with low calorie ingredients.

title: red raspberry cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, flour and raspberry jello.
Combine water and oil.
Add to the dry mixture. Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Stir in half the frozen raspberries.

title: loaf bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend eggs, milk and oil.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°
for 60 to 65 minutes, or until done.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: muffins
directions: Cream butter; add sour cream, then gradually add Bisquick. Grease miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: oven dinner casserole
directions: Place beans in greased baking dish.
Top with onions and potatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Pour soup over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Season with ground beef; place over vegetables in chunks. Bake uncovered about 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: four chips fudge
directions: Line a 10 1/2x15 1/2-inch jellyroll pan with aluminum foil, extending foil over ends of pan; grease foil.
Melt butter in a heavy Dutch oven over low heat; stir in sweetened condensed milk and milk.
Add all of the chips; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow creme and extracts.
Stir in walnuts. Spread mixture into prepared pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Use ends of foil to lift fudge from pan.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Yield:
12 dozen pieces.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-inch fluted tube or 10-inch tube pan.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix cheese and pineapple until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Garnish top with the nuts.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to a boil in a saucepan the butter, water and cocoa. Mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs, soda and sour cream in a bowl.
Add hot mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together with a fork. In a separate bowl, beat eggs with water. Gradually blend into flour mixture.

title: marshmallow dip
directions: Mix well using
enough pineapple juice to mix.
Use red and green apple
slices
for dipping.
Soak in pineapple juice before use to prevent browning.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together well.
Add sifted flour, salt and nutmeg alternately with chopped nuts to creamed mixture. Form into any desired shape: crescents, balls and rolls.
Bake about 20 minutes at 325°.
When done, cool on cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: the ritz-carlton's blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in eggs, milk and butter; do not overmix.
Carefully stir in berries.

title: knockwurst, hot german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Wash potatoes; dry and cut in half.
Place in plastic bag, cut side down; leave end of bag open.
Cook on High 10 minutes. Remove skins and slice.
Cook bacon and onion in 4 cup measure 4 or 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper. Mix well; add water, vinegar and celery seed.
Cook on High 4 minutes, stirring once.
Set aside; make several cuts in plastic bag containing knockwurst and place bag on paper plate; cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Arrange knockwurst on serving plate as well as potatoes; pour on hot sauce and toss to coat evenly. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: hot and spicy drummettes
directions: Heat oil and deep fry drummettes until golden brown.
Heat the hot sauce, butter and soy sauce in small pot and keep warm.
As drummettes get done, drain on paper towel and place in sauce for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Mix cheese and flour together.
Beat eggs and the light cream, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour 3/4 of the cheese mixture in pastry shell.
Add shrimp and remaining cheese. Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream and spread on crust.
Arrange sliced fruit on top. Drizzle with glaze.

title: ham dinner omelet
directions: Place 4 slices of the bread in a buttered mixing pan.
Mix green peppers, onions and mayonnaise.
Put mixture with ham and celery over bread in buttered pan.
Now put on second layer of bread.
Now pour mixture of eggs and milk over.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be made the night before.
This can be frozen.
This and a green salad make a fine supper, before church!

title: savory honey mustard sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add cranberries and 1 cup of cold water.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into gelatin mold or a glass Pyrex dish and refrigerate until set.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Roll in marble shape.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: hobo burgers
directions: Recipe Goal:
Complete dinner that's easy to make, can be prepared and refrigerated until baked, reheats in microwave in case of emergencies and easy to clean up.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Salt, pepper and flour pork chops.
Brown in oil in skillet. Place pork chops in a lightly greased baking dish; layer potatoes and onions.
Combine soup with 1/2 can water; pour over onions. Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cut cheese and margarine; let set at room temperature; then mix with fingers.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into balls and mash with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Take a package of sugar cookies and cut into quarters.
Grease a petite cupcake pan and place in each cup a quarter section of the cookie.
Bake according to directions.
While still hot, and before you remove from pan, take a small Reese's cup and put in center of each baked cookie.
Carefully remove from pan and rewrap in Reese's paper.
Great for parties.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Grease 3-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken breast in dish and top with cheese slices.
Mix soup with white wine and spoon over chicken.
Combine herb dressing mix with oleo and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add flour in three parts. Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in nuts, roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until very lightly brown on bottom.
Remove and roll in xxxx sugar.
Let cool and roll again in xxxx sugar.
Makes 25 to 30 cookies.

title: dr. carter's chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Place in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Spoon on soup and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat chocolate with water over very low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.

title: crab island spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Good on crackers at a buffet.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix everything, except cheese, and place in large casserole. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: banana chocolate loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and salt. Mix well. Dissolve baking powder and soda in the sour cream; add the first mixture.
Stir in banana pulp.
Add the flour gradually.
Add the vanilla and chocolate chips.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 70 minutes.
Can be served warm a la mode.
Freezes well.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in, but do not beat, the eggs, oil, vanilla, pineapple and bananas.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into three 9-inch well oiled and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Frost each layer and put nuts between and on top.

title: fish in aspic(fiskekabaret)
directions: Make gelatine according to directions.
Chill until almost set.
In a mold arrange choice of foods in a decorative pattern, shrimp, sliced hard-boiled eggs, crab meat, poached cod, cooked asparagus spears, peas or carrots.
Pour gelatine over mixture and chill.
Unmold to serve.
Serve with sauce.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Blend together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add pumpkin and pecans and mix well.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In a pan, put first 3 ingredients, bring to a boil and cook until clear.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Stir well.
Add sliced strawberries.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with fruit pulp and soda.
Add vanilla, nuts and fruit.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and sugar.
Let jell just so it wiggles.
Mix vanilla wafers and melted butter.
Put half on bottom of pan.
Whip the Carnation milk until very thick.
Add Jell-O mixture and whip a few minutes. Fold in drained crushed pineapple. Put on top of cookie mixture.
Add rest of cookies on top. Chill.

title: nutritious meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape any way you like. Cheese can be added to middle and then frozen.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat chocolate squares with 1/4 cup milk in microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Roll pieces of chicken in flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Fry in olive oil until done.

title: old-fashioned pennsylvania dutch strawberry shortcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter until you have coarse crumbs.
Combine beaten egg and light cream or buttermilk.
Add all at once to the crumb mixture and stir until just moist.
Spread dough in a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish and press a bit to build up the edges.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool slightly.
Slice shortcake to form 2 layers. Carefully lift top half.
Place the bottom half on an attractive serving dish.
Lightly butter the bottom layer.
Spoon about half of the berry mixture onto the shortcake.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Add flour to cookie dough and spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 350°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream in medium bowl until smooth.
Cut up slices of your favorite fruit.
Dip fruit in mixture and eat.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain and rinse; pour macaroni in a bowl.

title: dutch chocolate pie
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Beat the eggs in a large bowl.
Add the sugars and flour.
Blend until smooth.
Add the margarine. Blend again.
Stir the chocolate chips into the mixture.
Spoon the mixture into the pie shell.
Bake about an hour.

title: concetta's meat loaf(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix ingredients except for bacon and ham or salami. Add 1/2 can of sauce.
Layer 1/2 of meat in square baking dish.
Add more sauce and layer with ham or salami.
Top with rest of meat mixture.
Cover with remaining sauce and bacon.
Add 2 tablespoons oil.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until bubbly and cooked.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Fry turkey in oil until brown; add remainder of ingredients and simmer.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In medium bowl cream the cream cheese, jalapenos, onion, garlic and chili powder.
Fold in chicken and 1 1/2 cups of Jack cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
Spread mixture on insides of split pita bread.
Put on baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes, until very hot.
Cover with remaining cheese (Jack and Cheddar).
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Cut each pita half into 3 wedges.
Serve with salsa (optional).
Makes about 72 wedges.

title: maraschino cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix juice of cherries and cream cheese with electric mixer.
Cut up cherries and add.
Mix pineapple, marshmallows, whipped cream and sugar. Add to cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle
with nuts.
Let stand overnight.
Can be frozen.
Can be doubled.

title: christmas pudding 1
directions: Put all the dry ingredients into a very large mixing bowl and mix well.
Add all the wet ingredients, using enough milk to make a fairly soft consistency.
Mix all very well.
Divide mixture between 2 pudding basins (or 1 large if required).
Cover with greased greaseproof paper and steam for 8 hours, or steam in a pressure cooker for 30 minutes at pressure, then cook for 3 hours at 15 pounds pressure.
Makes 2 (1 1/2 pound size) puddings.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Place oil, mushrooms, onion and green pepper in frypan.
Brown vegetables.
Add tomato sauce and paste, garlic powder, sugar, pepper and oregano.
Cook on low heat.

title: carrot cake with pineapple
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add oil gradually. Add dry ingredients. Add pineapple and carrots. Add nuts and vanilla; blend well. Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1 cup crushed potato chips, broccoli, soup, cheese and 1 cup potato chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread onto flour tortillas.
Roll up. Chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Serve with extra salsa.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place dressing mix in dish.
Melt butter and pour over dressing.
Place chopped chicken on top.
Combine soups and broth. Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 15 minutes until brown.

title: caramel nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line pie crust with chopped pecans. Combine all other ingredients and pour over nuts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate and mix at room temperature.
Make a ball and roll in chili powder.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: party green beans
directions: In buttered 2-quart casserole dish alternately layer beans, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large
Dutch
oven,
cook fryer in water with onions and celery.
When
done,
remove
and debone chicken and place aside. Add
spaghetti
to
broth
and cook until broth is absorbed. Remove
from
heat
and add Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and stewed tomatoes.
Add deboned chicken and mix well.
Pour into large casserole
pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.
May
be divided into two pans and one frozen for future use.

title: pamie's pepperoni pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Add beaten egg; blend thoroughly.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour (don't open oven).
Allow pie to set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix and steam for 1 hour in a double boiler.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: new england pot roast
directions: Stir together flour, 1 tablespoon plus 2 teaspoons salt and pepper; rub mixture on meat.
Melt shortening in large electric skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat over medium heat, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; spread horseradish on both sides of meat. Add 1 cup water, cover tightly and simmer in electric pan or on top of range for 4 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in a saucepan.
Stir until well mixed.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk.
Stir milk into dry mixture.
Cook slowly on medium to low heat until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue or whipped topping.
Makes 1 pie.
May double recipe for 2 pies.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender until smooth and crystals have dissolved. Use in recipes calling for sweetened condensed milk. Equals one can.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large casserole pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sammie's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter together.
Cook on low heat 12 minutes or until it comes to boil (this should be soft ball stage).
Take off stove.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh peach pudding
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and margarine.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
In a large shallow glass casserole dish, place a layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with a layer of peach mixture. Continue layering until the peach mixture is used, ending with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with wafers and peach slices, if desired.

title: lemon ricotta cheese frosting
directions: Combine sifted xx sugar.
Combine cheese, margarine, juice and rind, beating until smooth.
Beat in xx sugar as needed for consistency for spreading.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Mix together flours, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir lightly into creamed mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans and bake until tests done.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date-nut spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
For finger sandwiches, cover one slice of brown wheat bread lightly with spread.
Top with another piece of brown wheat bread.
Remove crusts and cut each sandwich into thirds.

title: broiled orange roughy
directions: Rinse fish
and pat dry with paper towels.
Lay fillets on broiler
pan, coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion flakes, vegetable seasoning
and
paprika.
Marinate at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Place
in preheated broiler and broil for 8 to 10 minutes or	until
fish
flakes
with
a
fork.
Garnish
with chopped parsley and lemon wedges.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Unroll breadstick dough, separating into strips.
Working on a flat surface, coil one strip of dough around itself into a spiral pattern.
Add second strip of dough to the end of the first strip, pinching ends together to seal; continue coiling dough in a spiral pattern.
Repeat procedure with remaining dough strips to make an 8-inch flat circle.
Roll dough into a 13-inch circle and fit into a 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Fold edges under and flute; set prepared crust aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind apples, cranberries and orange.
Then add crushed pineapple to these in a bowl.
In a separate bowl dissolve the sugar, Jell-O and boiling water.
Let Jell-O mixture cool, then add fruit mixture.
I put about 1 cup chopped pecans in mine.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: smoked sausage and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut up one pint of strawberries into baked pie shell.
Mash up one pint of strawberries in saucepan.
Add sugar and cornstarch. Bring to a boil and allow to boil until mixture follows the spoon. Pour over strawberries in shell and cool.

title: caramel apple oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt; cut in margarine.
Press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add nuts to reserved crumb mixture.
In heavy pan, over low heat, melt caramels with sweetened milk, stirring until smooth.
Spoon apple filling over prepared crust; top with caramel mixture, then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with the salt and pepper.
Place chops in a shallow baking dish.
Place 2 tablespoons rice on top of each chop.
Cover chops with the basic tomato sauce.
Cover and place in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: lil's shrimp and pasta
directions: Saute shrimp in 1/4 cup olive oil until you can smell the shrimp.
Turn off fire and add Tony Chachere, seasoning and parsley.
Add can of shrimp soup and 1/2 cup water.
Let simmer on low.
Pour over pasta.

title: dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Fill jar with cucumbers.
Add garlic and dill.
Cover with boiling mixture.
Press out bubbles with knife.
Seal.

title: bacon and chive potato pancakes
directions: Peel the potato, grate it coarse and press it between several thicknesses of paper towel to remove any excess moisture.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 pan.
Line this with pecans and coconut.
Mix a German chocolate cake mix.
Pour over nuts and coconut in pan.
Mix oleo, confectioners' sugar, cream cheese, and vanilla together in a bowl until smooth.
Swirl around in the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with your favorite icing.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set in the middle.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Dump everything in one large mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into a long baking pan.
This is a large cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat shortening, egg and milk.
Add blueberries and salt.

title: diabetic french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; shake and serve.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix in eggs and almond extract. Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder, beating for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: forgotten souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch casserole.
Cover bottom with 2/3 of the bread cubes.
Sprinkle on half the cheese. Cover with ham, vegetables, remaining bread and cheese.
Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and pepper; mix.
Pour over mixture in casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover with foil during the last part to avoid browning.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together real good; start off in a cool oven.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine meal, margarine, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Mix well and cook until thick, stirring frequently. Remove from stove and add eggs, milk and baking powder.
Stir well. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
While warm, poke cake full of holes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, then ice cream topping. Let cool. (Can freeze.)
Top with whipped topping and pieces of candy.

title: quick crescent fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; press over bottom to form crust.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups nuts, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over crust.
Spread preserves evenly over crumb mixture. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine flour with next 4 ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over preserves. Bake at 375° for 22 to 28 minutes or until golden brown.
(Bars will be soft when removed from oven.)
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Yields 36 bars.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine cocoa and food coloring to make a paste. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla with a mixer. Add eggs and beat to blend. Add cocoa paste to mixture; beat well. Sift flour into a medium mixing bowl. Add flour alternately with buttermilk to the mixture. Beat well. Mix in vinegar. Pour batter into two 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool, split and frost. To split: Use thread or dental floss. Use a sawing motion to split each layer so there are 4 layers.

title: working girl buns
directions: Mix all, having dissolved yeast in a little warm water with 1/2 teaspoon sugar in it.
Add rest of ingredients; beat well and add balance of flour.
Knead and punch every hour, 6:00, 7:00, 8:00 and 9:00.
At 10:00, make into buns and let stand until morning.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water; stir in pie filling.
Turn into baking dish (13 x 8-inch) and chill until partly set.

title: apple cinnamon jelly
directions: Combine juice and pectin in large saucepan; bring to full boil.
Add sugar and candies, stirring constantly.
Bring to full boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let boiling subside and skim foam from top.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 7 1/2 pints.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Have eggs, butter and milk at room temperature.
Combine sugar, one cup at a time, with the softened butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Add flour which has been sifted 4 times to the creamed mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in milk and flavoring and pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: tasty dip or sandwich spread
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Also can be rolled into a ball and rolled in pecans.
Used as a tuna cheese ball.

title: quick bars
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a hard boil.
Add a small jar of peanut butter.
Add Special K corn flakes.
Pour over and drop on wax paper.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham and pork.
Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon toast(kids recipe)
directions: Place bread into a toaster.
When brown, spread butter on bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding into canned fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip topping. Add sliced bananas and top with slivered almonds.

title: one-pan blueberry cobbler(from comstock)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Add milk, biscuit mix and sugar; stir until smooth.
Drop spoonfuls of filling over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Separate lids; place in pan, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag; add to vinegar mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Place in bottom of each quart jar, 2 or 3 garlic cloves, 1 teaspoon mustard seed, 1 red pepper and a head of dill.
Pack cukes in jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Add another head of dill to top and pour boiling vinegar mix over, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe off rims of jars; place scalded lids on and screw bands firmly.
Next day, shake jars to blend flavors before storing in cool dark place for 6 weeks.

title: world's most wonderful cookies
directions: *Blended oatmeal - take 5 cups dry oatmeal and put in blender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Then add sugar and white syrup.
Stir until dissolved and boil until it will spin a thread.
Now add peanuts and cook slowly over a low fire until it turns a golden brown.
Take from fire and add butter, soda and vanilla.
Stir quickly.
Spread on 2 large cookie sheets, well buttered.
Set in cold place.
When set, break apart.

title: skillet pot roast
directions: Preheat skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Brown roast for 5 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Sprinkle roast with seasoned salt, pepper and soup mix.
Roast, covered, with vent closed for 2 or 2 1/2 hours.
Turn after 1 hour.

title: strawberry tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add next 3 ingredients. Stir in 1 tray of ice cubes until melted.
Spoon in sherbet. Serve immediately or let stand at room temperature.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party dogs
directions: Cut strips of bacon in half and cook slightly.
Cut wieners in half. Wrap partially cooked strip of bacon around wiener, securing with toothpick.

title: jam-filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in baking mix.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on
cookie
sheet,
ungreased.
Spread
slightly. Top each with 1/2 teaspoon
jam.
Drop	small
amount of dough onto jam.
Bake light brown,
to 12 minutes.
Cool, remove from sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
(Best to make day before serving.)

title: grandma's pancakes(one-half batch)
directions: Mix together and cook over medium heat.

title: beef barbecued sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add tomato puree, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Simmer over moderate heat 30 to 40 minutes.
Add about 20 medium slices of cooked beef or pork. Heat thoroughly, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut 10 hamburger buns in half; toast and butter lightly.
Serve meat on buns.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal, flour, eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: english toffee
directions: Prepare 2 buttered cookie sheets (medium size).
You will need 1 wooden spoon and 1 candy thermometer.

title: tossed salad
directions: Wash all vegetables; cut lettuce into bite size pieces.
Peel and cube carrots and cucumber.
Cut tops and bottoms from radishes and cube.
Seed bell pepper and cube.
Core and cube tomatoes.
Cut ends from celery and cube.
Toss all vegetables together.
Serve in individual salad bowls and top with dressing, bacon bits, ham, cheese and boiled eggs.
Add salt and pepper to individual taste.

title: easy hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, shortening, molasses and egg until smooth.
Mix spices, salt, soda, flour and raisins.
Add to the sugar shortening mixture with water to make a soft dough.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oats.
Stir melted margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Put about 3 cups of mixture in a 9-inch by 13-inch pan and press firmly.
Combine jam and water and spoon over crumb mixture; spread evenly.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture; make top even by patting firmly.

title: whoopie pies and icing
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Scramble sausage in heavy saucepan.
When cooked, sprinkle flour over sausage and drippings.
Cook over low heat until flour is cooked and slightly browned.
Pour hot milk over sausage mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Season to taste.
Serve over biscuits or toast points.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Stir bananas, sugar, milk, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowls until blended.
Stir in Bisquick and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack. Cool completely before slicing.

title: western kentucky style barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Use sauce to flavor chicken, pork or any meat.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Then add all ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 24 hour cabbage salad
directions: Combine in a medium saucepan celery salt, vinegar, mustard seed and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix crackers and margarine; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; chill. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crumbs; chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with Heath or Hershey bars sprinkled over Cool Whip.
May be frozen; thaws fast.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Boil all ingredients except cabbage.
Put cabbage in about 15 minutes before soup is done.
Makes about 3 gallons before cooked without cabbage; so a large pot is needed.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix well.
Before serving, add 1 (8 ounce) bottle Catalina dressing and Tostitos, broken up.
Mix well and serve.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat
Dream
Whip and milk approximately 10 minutes and then add pistachio pudding.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Slice off tops and hollow out. Cube bread. Fill bread with dip and chill for 24 hours. Serve with bread cubes, sticks, etc.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare potatoes for mashing and add butter and milk in quantity sufficient for smooth consistency. While still hot, add cream cheese and blend well.
Pour potatoes into baking dish and cover with strips of American cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a rectangular pan in a 425° oven until hot.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake chicken in flour mixture until coated.
Place skin side down in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: honey-cashew confections
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13x9 inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and salt in food processor; pulse until blended.
Add 1/2 cup butter; pulse until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Set aside.

title: crunchies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets with shortening. Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in small mixing bowl; mix well. Add to large mixing bowl and mix well. Stir in cereal. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Using pancake turner, place cookies on wire cooling rack. Cool cookies completely before starting, so they will stay crisp. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: carrot gold cake
