directions: Sift first five ingredients together, then add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend in thoroughly the carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
This bakes a large cake or 3 greased and floured 9-inch round layer tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for layers.

title: no bake chocolate drop cookies
directions: In a saucepan mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk; boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix well and quickly drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool until set (approximately 3 days).

title: bulgogi(korean stir-fry)
directions: Slice beef thinly, cutting against grain.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, water, green onion, garlic and pepper all together in a bowl.
Put sliced beef in mixture and mix with spoon. Marinate overnight for best result.
Stir-fry in saucepan or wok. Serve with rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef and vegetable stew for slow cooker
directions: About 10 hours before serving, quarter turnips and cut up carrots, combining them with all other ingredients in a 4 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker.
Mix well.
Cover; cook on low (180° to 200°) for about 10 hours.
Skim off fat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: freezer jams
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Combine water and Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Add mixture to fruit and stir 3 minutes.
Pour into jars or freeze in containers, leaving 1 inch from top of jar. Cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours. Freezer.
Yields 6 cups.
Will keep in fridge for 3 weeks.

title: hot tamale chili dip
directions: Mix all together and cook on medium heat until lumps are out.

title: wildly delicious turkey salad
directions: Combine water and contents of rice and seasoning packet in medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: like mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal (after measuring, put oatmeal in blender and blend until powder), salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Mix well, then add chocolate chips, Hershey bar (grated, shaved or cut into small chunks) and nuts.
Place golf ball size cookies 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Makes 112 large cookies or 50 very large cookies.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Yield:
4 servings. Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 7 g, fat 12 g, calories 155.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze in 1-gallon freezer.

title: savory cheese bites
directions: Combine cheese and breadcrumbs in a bowl.
Beat the eggs until frothy and mix in the salt, pepper and mustard.
Combine with the cheese mixture and form into small balls.
If mixture is too moist, add a little more soft breadcrumbs, but do not make the texture too dry and crumbly to coat.
Heat oil for deep frying in wok and when hot, fry a few of the cheese balls at a time on medium heat until they are golden brown all over.
Lift out and drain on absorbent paper.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat for 3 minutes.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch square pan, greased and floured.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Cut in the oleo.
Stir in pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Soak ham in cold water in the refrigerator 6 hours or overnight (if country ham is not available, use a commercially cured ham that is not fully cooked, if possible and don't soak). Drain; pat dry.
Remove any rind or excess fat.
Cut edges at 1-inch intervals about 1/8-inch deep.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Brush a 12-inch skillet with bacon drippings or cooking oil.
Heat over medium heat.
Add meat; fry about 12 to 15 minutes per side or until crispy, reducing heat to medium-low, if necessary, to keep the meat from burning.

title: tarragon pork chops
directions: Trim fat and bone from chops.
Pat dry.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan over medium/low heat.
Add meat.
Cook for 6 minutes on each side.
Check for doneness.
Cook longer, if necessary.

title: whole dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jars along with dill, garlic and onion. Boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over pickles.
Let sit until change of color, then drain and boil again and pour over pickles and seal your jars.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, Miracle Whip and vanilla; add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes (at 350°) or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes. Melt caramels with milk over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Top crust with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved 1 cup batter by teaspoonfuls over pecans.
Continue baking 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Place garlic cloves in blender or food processor and crush. Add remaining ingredients, store in refrigerator.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: cheesy tuna 'n rice muffinlettes
directions: Combine rice, cheese, tuna, olives, onion, parsley and salt. Stir in eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly.
Spray 6 muffin cups with Pam.
Divide rice mixture evenly among cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Loosen with spatula and arrange on a serving plate.

title: cubed steak and rice
directions: Brown cubed steak.
Pour soup and milk over steak and simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: another apple crisp
directions: Put apples, water and lemon juice in Pyrex dish; blend together brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter. Spread on top of apples and bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, water and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boil.
Continue without stirring until temperature reaches 280°.
Gradually stir in peanuts so mixture keeps boiling.
Cook until temperature reaches 300°; add baking soda, blend quickly.
Immediately turn onto greased baking sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: quick pie
directions: Put fruit in a buttered dish and cover with bread slices. Mix egg, sugar and butter. Pour on top of bread. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet and cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; beat and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: washing church dressing
directions: Mix in order given.
Shake thoroughly and let stand overnight. Yields 1 quart.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
(Chicken can either be cooked immediately or put in refrigerator to marinate.)
Saute chicken in oil.
Serve over rice.

title: emma's round steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Roll each piece in flour, salt and black pepper to taste.
Brown in frypan.
Drain steak of grease.
Put into baking pan with lid.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all together and pour half of batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix filling for cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend in a large mixing bowl the sugar, flour, cream cheese, vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Beat in eggs and egg yolks one at a time.
Add whipping cream and beat well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then lower to 250° and bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: cajun or creole seasoning
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered container.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice; put aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups of liquid.
In a saucepan, bring mixture to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken. Debone and set aside.
Cook 2 cups instant rice in 2 cups chicken broth from cooking chicken.
Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute onion in oil.
Add tomato sauce, sour cream and chicken.
Heat through and place on top of rice. Cover with crushed nacho chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish heaven
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add the other ingredients and chill.
Mix a day ahead.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello according to package.
Add 1/2 cup more of water than package says.
Add cranberry sauce.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes, then add chopped walnuts.

title: risotto di scampi (shrimp risotto)
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons of butter and the oil in a heavy skillet or casserole.
Stir in the garlic and rice until golden.
Add wine; cook over low heat.
Add half of broth and cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt, pepper, marjoram and remaining broth.
Stir lightly with a fork.
Re-cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat or until rice is tender and dry.
Stir in cheese and remaining butter. Serves 4 to 6.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops with flour, salt and pepper.
Combine soup, water and rosemary.
Pour over pork chops.
Sprinkle with half of the onion rings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with other half of onion rings.
Cook some egg noodles. Take pork chops out of juice; blend sour cream with juice in pan. Put noodles in pan with pork chops on top and rewarm.

title: coq au vin
directions: Heat oil in oven-safe casserole dish on medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and saut until brown (3 to 5 minutes). Add dressing mix and onions. Stir in wine and brown and cook until blended. Add chicken; cover and reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes. Flip chicken halfway through. Remove chicken. Increase heat to high and boil sauce until slightly thickened. Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together,
soda,
salt
and
baking powder and set aside. Cream
shortening, add white sugar, cream together and add brown sugar
and
cream.
Add
eggs
one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour mixture all at once and mix.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Add chocolate and mix.
(Can also use raisins or
coconut.)
Grease
cookie
sheets.
Drop with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: crab mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in boiler.
Add soup and heat until it bubbles.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into oiled mold and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce and garnish.

title: tuna puffy sandwich
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except the egg white.
Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into the tuna mixture.
Spread over English muffin halves; broil until puffy.
Serve immediately.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer as given.
Top with Hellmann's, sealing to edge. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute bacon, onion and pepper.
Add potatoes, vegetables, water and bouillon.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Add salmon, milk, corn and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.

title: margaret's chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Cook onion, pepper and celery in chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Mix spaghetti and 2/3 of cheese.
Add soup, vegetables and broth, pimentos, chicken and seasonings.
Pour into 1 large or 2 small buttered casseroles.
Place remaining cheese on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese stand in bowl until soft add sour cream, sugar.
Beat with beater until smooth add eggs and vanilla mix until smooth.
Use a 9 x 13 pan.
Spared rolls into pan, press thinly together.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.

title: friendship spice tea
directions: Mix together.
To make a cup of tea use 2 teaspoons of mix to one cup hot water.
Use less sugar if so desired.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in fat; remove from pan.
Simmer onion and green pepper in remaining fat.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Mix onion, pepper, pimentos and 1 can of soup.
Add rice. Put rice mixture in casserole dish.
Put pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover with remaining can of soup.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or until pork chops are done.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scoop insides from peppers.
Parboil the peppers for 5 to 10 minutes; set aside.
Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Chop onion and saute in butter.
Prepare rice by directions on box.
Mix together the hamburger, onion, rice and Cheez Whiz.
(Keep about 1/4 cup Cheez Whiz out to use later.)

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets; save liquid.
In a medium saucepan, bring beet liquid and remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes; pour over beets.
If there is not enough liquid to cover beets, make up the difference with boiling water.
(This recipe should fill a 1-quart jar.)
Chill for several days to allow flavors to blend before serving.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Saute the vegetables in the butter until they are tender, stirring often (about 15 minutes).
Stir in the seasonings and flour.
Add tomatoes, milk, tuna and parsley.
Heat and continue stirring, until soup is thickened.
Add cheese, if desired.

title: west virginia skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add eggs, dates and sugar. Stir and cook on low heat about 5 minutes after it starts to boil. Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Cool; shape into logs or walnut size balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion salt, salt and sugar.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15
minutes.
If
cheese
is desired, sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake for 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: salmon ball
directions: In medium bowl flake salmon, removing bones and skin.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley; mix well.
Refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm enough to shape into a ball.
Shape into ball; roll in parsley.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving. Serve with assorted crackers or small slices of rye bread.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix whipped topping, sour cream, sugar and evaporated milk. Add cake to mix and pour in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Make topping by mixing strawberries and glaze.
Spread over cake and refrigerate.

title: broccoli corn bread(low-fat version)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cottage cheese; mix well. Lightly stir in cottage cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Slice vegetables into small bite size pieces. Slice olives.
Prepare salad dressing mix as directed on envelope. Combine pasta, vegetables, olives, cheese and salad seasoning in a large bowl.
Add prepared salad dressing.
Toss.
Chill 2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Place in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: muddie buddies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine together. Pour cereal into large bowl.
Pour melted chocolate mixture over cereal and stir until coated.
Put into very large Baggie.
Pour powdered sugar in and shake all about until coated.

title: lillie's potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Place in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or longer.

title: beef fried rice(mexican style)
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, bell pepper and garlic over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink (breaking up into 1/2 to 3/4-inch crumbs).
Pour off drippings.
Season with chili powder and salt.

title: the governor's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using your hands, "squish" all ingredients together (as if you're making a mud pie).
Form into loaf.
Place on baking rack or in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes (until done).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all
together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mini sour cream biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into greased mini muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown. Makes 1 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add other ingredients; stir often.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: extra easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and drain blueberries.
Place in bottom of 10 x 6-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix next 4 ingredients with fork until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Distribute flour mixture over blueberries.
Drizzle top with butter.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes; do not overbake.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring Jell-O, water, sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Pour over diced cream cheese.
Stir until cream cheese is mixed through. Set in refrigerator until about like milk shake (1 to 2 hours). Then stir in Cool Whip and pour in Jell-O mold.
Let sit overnight.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions.
Drain and cool by running under cold water.
Add chopped chicken, green and black olives and peppers.
Stir well.
Stir in Viva Italian dressing. The different colored peppers add a lot of color!
Serve chilled.

title: wild duck gumbo
directions: Boil duck until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
Brown duck pieces in hot oil.
Set aside.

title: dicksies chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, chiles, soup, cheese and sour cream.
Fill tortillas; top with cheese, soup and olives (mixed).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peppery chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish.
Pour teriyaki sauce over chicken; cover and chill 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade. Combine thyme and next 4 ingredients; sprinkle evenly over chicken.
Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook half of chicken 5 to 10 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat this procedure to cook remaining chicken.

title: magnificent mushroom treat
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop 1/2 cup of stems. Mix these with cheese mixture.
Saute mushroom caps in butter or white or red wine.
Fill caps with cheese mixture and place under broiler for 3 to 6 minutes.

title: cool soup gazpacho espanol
directions: In the blender, put the garlic, salt, vinegar, cucumber, tomato, oil and bread with 1/2 cup of water.
Beat for 1 minute, then put in a bowl everything from the blender.
Add the water, salt and vinegar.
It depends on individual taste.
You may need to add more of each.

title: pork chop skillet dinner
directions: Brown chops; remove from skillet and drain fat.
Spread rice over bottom of skillet.
Add water and salt.
Arrange chops over rice.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Spoon on corn.
Add pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: all-meat chili spread
directions: If desired, brown ground chuck in skillet to remove excess fat. Otherwise, skim off top before serving.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; stir thoroughly to mix spices.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 10 hours.
Serve topped with fresh chopped onions.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix just before serving.

title: roast chicken in a brown paper bag
directions: Get a whole chicken or chickens for your family.
Wash and dry; butter well and season with salt and pepper.
Stick in a heavy paper bag, fold it closed and put in a shallow baking dish or pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
When you take out, just tear the bag away and get out the chicken.
It will be completely done and even a little brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except hamburger.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Brown hamburger, drain.
Add meat last.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients, except vanilla.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix the first three ingredients.
When mixed, place about 1/2 teaspoon into liners of midget muffin tins.
Beat all ingredients with electric mixer until smooth; pour over crumbs, until 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cherry cola salad(good!)
directions: Mix together pie filling, sugar and water.
Add jello, pineapple, nuts and Coke.
Stir well.
Chill overnight or at least 3 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat flour, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden.
Prepare filling by stirring eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans. Spread evenly over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until set.
Cool.
Makes 60 (1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Melt butter. Add cheese, garlic, paprika, parsley, and oregano. Pour over bread and toss lightly. Bake at 200° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and seal in airtight container.

title: mexican corn zucchini dish
directions: Slice zucchini and cut kernels from corn.
Combine zucchini, corn, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring gently over medium heat, for 10 to 12 minutes until zucchini and corn are cooked.

title: favorite nacho dip (meatless)
directions: Spread beans over a plate or dish with slightly raised edge. Mix taco seasoning with sour cream until well blended.
Spread over beans.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; place in shallow casserole dish; add mushroom soup, undiluted; pepper and cheese.
Place pats of butter on top. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot apple cider(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Brew ingredients in 30-cup percolator as if for coffee.
Use a filter for clearer brew.
Serve hot.
Makes about 24 cups.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry
ingredients
with
a little milk.
Add rest of milk. Cook
over	boiling water, stirring until thick.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer,	stirring
occasionally.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add a little of the hot mixture to egg yolks. Pour back and cook a few minutes
longer.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour filling into
shell.
Cool slightly.
Cover with meringue. Bake at 325° for 12 to
15	minutes.
Makes
6 servings.

title: christmas morning cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and flour, tossing to coat.
Add 1 cup sugar, mixing well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole
dish. Combine oatmeal, chopped pecans, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar; add butter and stir well.
Spoon over fruit mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with cranberries and pecan pieces before baking.

title: beef or pork and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Trim
fat
from meat.
Slice across the grain into thin strips about 1-inch wide and 3-inches long.
(Partially frozen meat is easier to slice.) Heat oil in frypan.
Add meat strips and stir-fry over high heat, turning pieces constantly, until no longer
red
(3 to 5 minutes).
Reduce heat.
Add carrots, celery, onions
and seasonings.
Cover and cook until carrots are slightly
tender
to
4 minutes).
Mix cornstarch and water. Add slowly to beef mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: diabetic chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat 2 minutes at high speed. Measure together remaining ingredients (except nuts).
Blend into first mixture on low speed for 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Spread into greased 8-inch pan to edges.
Dip slightly in center.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: super nacho
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water. Spread bean dip to cover bottom of a pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with meat; sprinkle with chilies.
Broil for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and brown.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, guacamole and chips.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine lentils and water.
Let soak 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 30 minutes in microwave.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Lightly brown onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients except hot dogs.
Place hot dogs in baking dish.
Pour sauce over dogs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting several times.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Stir in pudding.
Beat with beater until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs and chill until firm. Top with cherry pie filling.
Serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: quick (microwave) barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape into loaf in 12 x 8-inch baking dish (microsafe).
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until center is no longer pink, turning dish after 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with remaining barbecue sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; add soup and sour cream.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pour half of this mixture into a dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Keep other half of mixture in bowl at room temperature for top layer.

title: four bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the beans, green peppers and onions.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir until the sugar dissolves. Pour over the bean mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring several times.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour hot water over broccoli.
Break apart and drain well. Mix broccoli with crushed crackers in a buttered 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.

title: dressed up pork chops
directions: Season chops and brown quickly in shortening.
Place chops in flat baking dish.
Place rice, pepper and tomato slices on chops and add hot water to skillet where chops were browned.
Pour over chops and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove; immediately add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet or waxed paper.
You may press top with fork or leave as you drop them.
Cool; enjoy.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cheyene (wacky) cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make 3 wells.
Put vanilla in one, vinegar in one and oil in another.
Pour 2 cups water over all.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not remove from pan.
Frost when cool.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Precook noodles; drain. Mix all ingredients with noodles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange in greased 14 x 7 inch baking dish. Sprinkle water chestnuts over broccoli and place chicken on top of water chestnuts.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top of all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-enchilada casserole
directions: Cook seasoned chicken in microwave (1/2 chicken for 12 minutes on 1 side on High in microwave, then turn to other side for 12 minutes in microwave).
Let cool, debone and cut into small pieces.

title: ruth lyons kartoffelsalat(german potato salad)
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel and dice, and keep warm.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Measure 1/4 cup bacon fat and return to skillet.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, mustard and sugar; heat and pour over hot potatoes.
Add eggs and pickle relish and mix lightly to blend.
Serve immediately.

title: plant food
directions: Stir into 1 gallon of tepid water.
Use once every 4 to 6 weeks.

title: chyrel's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, cooked rice and Cheez Whiz. Mix well.
Pour over cooked broccoli in casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and leave stems on.
Pack in jars, stems up.
Place 1 pepper pod and 1 garlic clove in each jar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and milk. Blend until very smooth and add vanilla and confectioners sugar. Fold in topping. Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crusts and freeze until ready to serve. Will make 2 large pies or 3 small ones.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix and sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy fudge cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Boil over low heat cocoa, water, margarine and Crisco.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Heat butter, milk and flour until thick, stirring constantly. Add egg yolks to thicken milk.
Add crabmeat and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs for a dry mixture.
Spread over casserole and sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry smoothies
directions: In a blender container, combine strawberries, lemonade or limeade concentrate and powder sugar.
With blender running, add ice cubes, one at a time, through the opening in the lid until the mixture is slushy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef and cheese crescent pie
directions: In pan, brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green beans, garlic and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes. Use crescent rolls to make crust in ungreased pie pan.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese and spread over crust.
Spoon in meat mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: settler beans
directions: Mix all and bake or heat in large pot or slow cooker.

title: chili
directions: Brown lightly the ground beef, onion and minced garlic.
Then add tomatoes and chili powder to taste.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Then add red kidney beans, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all by hand in large bowl.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add the eggs and beat well. Add the pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350° until lightly browned. Serves 6.
Can be served as a meat accompaniment, hot or cold.

title: margie's cheese cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch spring-form pan and press graham cracker mixture into bottom of pan with a flat-bottomed glass.

title: crab bake
directions: Melt one tablespoon butter in saucepan and cook red pepper until soft.
Add cream, bread crumbs, seasonings, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Gently mix in crab meat. Place in casserole and top with a little paprika.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix the last 7 ingredients in a small bowl.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in butter.
Remove excess fat from pan.
Add sauce to hamburger mixture; mix well.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Combine soup, broccoli, tomato, sour cream and mustard in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve.
Use crackers and chips to dip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and garlic until tender.
Drain and mash. Place in greased casserole dish in layers with cheese and crackers.
Pour on combined egg and milk.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix separately the sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or 10-inch round serving dish, layer ingredients in the following order:
avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Top with jalapenos.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: congealed salad
directions: Simmer 1/2 cup of water with the pineapple juice drained from the can.
Add jello and stir while it is simmering until it is dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and milk; beat with mixer.
Add nuts, cherries, pineapple and cheese.
Put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add fruits and nuts. Spoon half into pan or mold.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream or softened cream cheese over salad.
Cover with remainder of salad mixture. Chill until firm.

title: grubons(instead of croutons)
directions: When collecting your lettuce and greens from your garden, don't throw away those nasty, little grubs that are chomping down your produce.
Separate the assorted grubs from the greenery and dry on a towel.
Saute the grubs until crisp in the olive oil, chopped garlic and salt.
Grubons add a tasty garnish to your salad!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, leaving crisp.
Combine remaining ingredients. Layer broccoli in casserole dish. Pour mixture over broccoli. Allow to fill between broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts, if desired.
Freeze until firm and serve.
Serves 8.

title: beer and kraut fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and add vanilla and beat.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture, alternating with beer and beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Stir in the sauerkraut.
Turn into two greased and floured layer cake pans. Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool on rack and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: flop cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Add pineapple and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angie baldoni's chocolate meringues
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler or over very low heat. Remove from heat. Preheat oven to 325°. Beat egg whites and a pinch of salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar, beating at high speed until stiff. Beat in cider vinegar and vanilla. Fold in melted chocolate and chopped nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake about 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies feel firm when touched. Let cool for a few minutes, then remove to rack.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add sugar, raisins, caraway seed and margarine.
Blend well and then add buttermilk and eggs.
Stir and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
I use a black-iron frying pan; any heavy, round pan will do.
Cool and wrap to keep.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add Ragu; let simmer.
Drain noodles.

title: sausage and chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute sliced pepper, onion and hot sausage in butter for 5 minutes.
In 9 x 13 pan, mix consumme and rice.
Add meat mixture. Place chicken breast on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole for brunch
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Cook noodles; heat corn. Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together.
Add ground beef, noodles and corn.
Put in a large casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except catsup and shape into loaf.
Place in container; top with catsup.
Microwave on High for 16 minutes, rotating every 4 minutes.

title: cornflake cookie candy
directions: In large bowl, mix cornflakes and peanut butter together.
In small saucepan, heat syrup and sugar until it reaches a boil. Take off heat and pour over cornflake mixture.
Shape into balls and place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Put 6 tortillas in 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brown meat.
Add salt, garlic salt and chili powder to taste in meat.
Spread meat over the tortillas; add chopped onion.
Spread beans.
Slice entire box of cheese and layer over beans.
Add 6 remaining tortillas and add the cream of chicken soup (full strength).
Then add tomatoes. Cover tightly with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 3 1/2 cups water to boil.
Stir in chicken bouillon until dissolved.
Combine cornstarch and remaining 1/2 cup water; add to bouillon, stirring constantly. Mix in tarragon.
Cook and stir until thickened and boiling.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Reduce heat to low; gradually add Egg Beaters in a thin stream, without stirring.
Cook for 30 seconds.
Stir once or twice.
Serve in bowls garnished with scallions.

title: creamy kiwi cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs for two 8-inch layer cakes.
Bake and cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Sear thoroughly until meat is crumbled, then combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Remove bay leaf; serve over spaghetti.
Serves 7.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients; add them alternately to zucchini.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Put batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake for 75 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oleo, milk, vanilla, sugar and cocoa to boiling in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Stir in oats.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, put melted butter.
Add flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Set aside and cool completely.
After it is cool, crumble and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix egg whites, strawberries, sugar and lemon juice until stiff (it should form a peak).
Fold in Cool Whip and put on top of crumbled mixture.
Put in freezer when not serving.
Cut in squares.
Good as a salad or dessert.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until creamy. Add salt and flour. Mix. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts. Turn mixture into greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Garnish with powdered sugar.

title: garden blend casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain well.
Put in casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: almond meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in almonds and almond extract.
Drop meringue by heaping spoonfuls 1 inch apart onto wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets.
Remove from waxed paper and cool completely on wire racks.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 6 minutes.
Allow to cool completely.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes for 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Complete cooling on wire rack.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Generously butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread crumbs and sprinkle cheese over.
Add beaten eggs over bread and cheese/bread mixture in pan.
Sprinkle bacon and mushrooms over top.
Chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
(If it starts to brown, put foil over it.)
Will serve 10 to 12 people.

title: mona's mexican baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain and mix with all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: aunt ola's pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour in pie shells and bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken veggie flautas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Butter one side of tortilla. Place mixture on buttered side of tortilla.
Roll up tortilla and place, seam side down, on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and hot sauce.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Drain and mash hearts well.
Add crumbs, cheese and eggs.
Add finely chopped garlic to heated olive oil; watch carefully.
When garlic has softened, add all of first mixture and stir until heated through.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in bread crumbs and cheese until slightly coated.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat
chili,
minced garlic and minced jalapeno pepper. Simmer 5
minutes.
Stir
grated cheese into hot chili mixture until cheese
dissolves.	Transfer dip to chafing dish.
Serve hot with Fritos or Doritos.	Dip may be made ahead of serving time and reheated.

title: italian tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, spinach, corn, Ricotta and egg.
Place 1/2 cup mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; arrange seam-side down in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: cheddar cheese snacks(microwave)
directions: Place the 8 Triscuits or crackers on a china or pottery 10-inch dinner plate.
Make sure plate has no metal trim.
Top each cracker with cheese square, then each cheese square with olive slice.
Cook in microwave oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is just melted on "Low".

title: squash patties
directions: Place grated squash, onion, salt, pepper, flour, egg and cornmeal into a bowl and mix well.
Form into patties and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: fruit 'n cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Layer in sundae glasses with fruit pie filling.
Chill in freezer for 30 minutes, then keep in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix cheese with this while still hot.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple and nuts.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until well mixed.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add sugar and mix until thickened.
Dough will be soft. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and then stamp cookie flat.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Remove from sheet at once.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in pot of salted water 15 minutes.
Drain eggs.
Let cool.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks.
Mash them together with the remaining ingredients except paprika.
Spoon mixture into egg whites.
Sprinkle top of eggs with paprika.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello in large bowl; stir until jello is dissolved.
Stir in vinegar and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Break up corned beef and stir into other ingredients, then stir into jello.
Place in oiled mold.
Serve on large platter covered with salad greens.
This makes an excellent luncheon salad.

title: broccoli marinated
directions: Combine and marinate for 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add meat, salt and pepper. Shape into 14 to 16 medium balls.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Double sauce ingredients when serving with pasta.

title: jolly chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken pieces on outside and drain.
Pour off all possible grease and add water for rice into chicken crumbs in skillet.
In a casserole large enough to lay chicken on top of rice, place amount of Minute rice for number of servings and add boiling water from skillet in the same amount.
Let stand, covered, a bit.
Lay browned chicken on top and cover.
Place in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: salmagundi, baked fish newburg
directions: Cook fish for 10 minutes in salted water and drain.
Melt margarine in glass (quart measure) in microwave.
Stir in flour and milk. Microwave 1 minute and stir.
Microwave another minute and stir until thickened. Stir in grated cheese and sherry.
Put fish and lobster or other seafood into greased baking dish.
Pour white sauce over the fish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter milk
directions: Combine milk solids and sugar; add cold water and shake or beat until smooth.
Add a small amount of mixture to peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Continue adding milk until all the mixture is used.
Chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Salad is better after being refrigerated overnight.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, combine oil and chili powder.
Cook 1 minute over medium heat.
Increase heat to medium high.
Add half of chicken pieces and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cook 4 minutes, stirring frequently with a slotted spoon.
Remove chicken to a large bowl.
Repeat with other half of chicken and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook onions, chilies and cumin for 5 minutes in drippings.
Spoon mixture into bowl with chicken.
Add tomato, pinto beans and remaining salt.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef in bottom of shallow casserole. Wrap a strip of bacon around each chicken breast. Arrange over dried beef. Spread undiluted soup over chicken. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Increase heat to 350° and bake for another 20 to 30 minutes, basting several times. Yield: 6 servings.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and dice the artichoke hearts.
Combine all ingredients together; mix together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (or until brown).
Serve with crackers.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add medium bag of crushed Fritos.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the vanilla, baking powder and crumbs with milk.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook spinach and squeeze out moisture.
Melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms until soft.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add sifted together dry ingredients and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Grate or chop fine the cucumber, sweet pepper, onion and carrots.
Stir all in partially congealed jello at least 24 hours before serving; keep chilled.
Especially good with dried beans and meats.

title: oven-baked french toast
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Slice bread 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick slices and place over syrup mixture.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until done.
Drain.
Prepare as you would regular mashed potatoes, adding cheese.
Put into baking dish and bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Put cabbage, onions and pepper in a bowl in order of ingredients. DO NOT STIR.
Sprinkle sugar on top. Bring oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Pour over above. DO NOT STIR.
Let sit overnight.
Stir and serve.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In a large saucepan, heat soup and milk to boil.
Add vegetables.
Return to a boil.
Cover.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.

title: chili
directions: Cook onion and ground beef. Drain. Mix other ingredients into hamburger mixture and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice and heat until thickened.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot and chop onion. Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Pour over cabbage.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash potatoes.
Add butter, condensed milk, eggs, extract, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Beat until smooth. Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and if desired, serve with whipped topping.

title: zucchini with baby carrots(light recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini in a skillet.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini, cover and cook 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
(Add additional water, 1 tablespoon at a time, if necessary, to prevent sticking.)

title: steak diane
directions: Combine oleo and Worcestershire sauce in a large skillet. Place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute until tender.
Place steak between plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard on one side of each steak.
Cook steaks, mustard side down, 4 minutes over medium heat.
Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard on top side, then flip.
Cook 4 minutes or until desired doneness.
Lightly pierce steak with forks.
Pour brandy over steaks, cover and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon mushroom mixture over steaks.

title: e-z chocolate frosting
directions: Add hot water to butter and blend.
Add vanilla and cocoa; blend.
Add sugar; adjust by adding a little more sugar or water to get the right consistency.
Makes a boxed cake mix taste great!

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with any seafood. Best if made the day before to be used.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Preheat well greased 8 x 10 inch heavy skillet in 425 degree oven, or grease an 8 x 8 inch baking pan.
Blend all ingredients and pour into skillet or pan.
Bake in 425 degree oven for:

title: choco-cherry nut drop cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add firmly packed brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Cream well.
Blend in unbeaten egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted Pillsbury's Best self-rising flour gradually, blending well.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet chocolate morsels, nuts (chopped) and 1/4 cup cherries.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce and place in 4-quart shallow bowl.
Top with onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Open the package of peas and break apart; sprinkle over the salad.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder. Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with eggs and bacon.
Will keep for days.

title: cheese and fruit salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in salad bowl.
Sprinkle with orange jello. Add oranges and pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping to desired consistency.

title: sausage balls(southern cannon balls)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into bite sized balls. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. (May be frozen and baked when needed.)

title: pine nut brie
directions: Dip Brie in scrambled egg, then in bread crumbs.
Saute Brie in olive oil until golden brown.
Place on serving plate.
Remove oil from pan.
Wipe out pan with paper towel.
Place pine nuts in pan.
Cook pine nuts over medium heat until golden brown.
Pour pine nuts over Brie and serve with crackers on French bread.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: choco-caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan over low heat.
Mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, oleo and pecans.
Press half of this mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramel layer.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak strips with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil along with onion and garlic.
Stir in with meat while browning. When nicely browned, add green peppers and bouillon.
Simmer about 10 minutes, then add drained tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes. Meanwhile, mix soy sauce and water with cornstarch.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens and serve with hot fluffy rice. Double the recipe to serve 4.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Combine breadcrumbs and next 3 ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg substitute; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.

title: very berry slushie
directions: Mix raspberries, ice cubes and sugar in a blender for 3 minutes.
Add water and mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into glasses. Serves 4.

title: french market beignets
directions: Heat milk in saucepan to scalding stage.
Do not scorch it; stir often.
Place shortening in mixing bowl.
Add sugar.
Pour in the scalded milk and stir until ingredients are melted.
Cool to lukewarm stage.
Add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Sift dry ingredients (salt, nutmeg and flour).
Gradually add approximately 1/2 of flour mixture to milk mixture to form batter.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Stir in remaining flour to mixture.
Cover and allow to double in bulk (1 hour).
Knead gently.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in diamond shapes.
Fry in hot oil, turning once.
Drain and dust with powdered sugar.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet; pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer 30 minutes. Cook lasagna noodles in salted water.
Drain carefully.
Grease long rectangular baking dish.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue layers and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, but withhold 2 ounces of cheese to crumble into mixture.

title: vichy carrots
directions: Cook carrots, butter, sugar and fresh parsley in saucepan with just enough water to cover the carrots.
Cover and simmer.
When water is just about evaporated, carrots should be done, approximately 20 minutes.
(Good side dish.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for at least 1 hour. Salt and pepper according to your taste.
Enjoy!

title: carrot cheese ring salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 3/4 cup.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple and cheese in bowl.
Mix juice, flour and sugar in separate bowl. Mix until smooth. Combine with pineapple and cheese.
Spoon into well greased casserole dish.

title: cabbage with smoked ham hocks
directions: Simmer the ham hocks until tender in large pot (half full of water).
When the cabbage has been picked, washed and cut into small pieces, place in pot with ham hocks.
Cook about 30 minutes. Add hot pepper, onion, sugar and vinegar.
Continue cooking over low heat until all is tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls. Coat if desired with chocolate or roll in toasted coconut or chopped nuts.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips with milk and salt over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 9-inch aluminum foil-lined pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Brown hot dogs in a little oil.
Add onions and green pepper and saute.
Add tomato sauce and other seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine with noodles.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts and starts to bubble.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: On low heat, mix sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Let simmer on low until mixture forms firm ball in glass of cold water.
This can be done by taking approximately 1/2 teaspoon of mixture and dropping it in water.
When the firm ball forms, remove immediately from heat.
Add vanilla and beat in the peanut butter until completely mixed in, then pour into buttered-greased pan. Set in refrigerator until hardens.
Slice into squares.

title: cocoa bake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Cool the mixture and pour over the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in an 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter into hot skillet, making 4-inch circles for each pancake.
Yields approximately 9 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Toss pineapple and cheese.
Mix flour and sugar separately; stir into pineapple and mix well.
Pour into baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter; spoon over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar; mix in egg, sour cream, and vanilla. Melt 1 c. chocolate chips and blend with creamed mixture.

title: butternut squash with ginger
directions: Peel and seed the squash.
Cut it into 1/2-inch cubes.
Put the squash, ginger root and apple juice into a lightly-oiled baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle on the nutmeg just before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Place in large pot.
Add vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add salt to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch or three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or four 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans. In large bowl cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake about 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into wax mixture.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs one at a time; beat well. Sift dry ingredients. Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream into shortening mixture. Grease and flour a tube pan. Place 1/2 of batter, 1/2 filling; remaining batter and filling on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bill's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and corn meal.
Add eggs, oleo, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat bran bread
directions: Melt yeast in warm water.
Add salt, honey, cereal and wheat germ.
Add 5 cups of whole wheat flour; stir.
Add flour gradually until dough is pliable and elastic.
Knead dough about 1 minute. Let dough rise until doubled in size.
Punch down; knead for a minute, then put into loaf pans.
Let rise again until doubled in size.
Pot it in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until it pulls away from the sides of the pan.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain pimento.
In a bowl, mix chilies, cheeses, artichoke hearts and mayo. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle more Parmesan and the pimento on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh cauliflower soup
directions: Core cauliflower, remove leaves and separate into small pieces.
Combine cauliflower pieces, onion and chicken broth in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until cauliflower is tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Remove and reserve about 1/3 of the cauliflower.
Transfer remaining mixture to a food processor or blender and puree until smooth.

title: sweet*10 cookies(for diabetics)
directions: Blend all together.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix eggs, peas, turkey and noodles.
Alternate layers of turkey mixture, soup and cheese in casserole.
Reserve 2 tablespoons cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Dissolve dressing mix in oil and pour over pretzels.
Stir several times until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: super hamburg sloppy joe
directions: Put hamburg in large skillet and brown, stirring to break up meat.
Drain off fat.
Add soup, relish and other seasonings.
Cook until blended, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: quick shrimp
directions: Prepare rice by box directions. Heat cream of onion soup with 1/2 can water and 1/2 can milk. Add shrimp. Simmer 2 minutes. Add seasoning. Pour over hot rice.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and 1 cup bread cubes.
Pile lightly into individual baking dishes or casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and remaining bread cubes. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mixed veggies and cheese dish
directions: Place in preheated wok or frypan at 300°.
Saute garlic, onions and green pepper in oil until transparent.
Add carrots and zucchini.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add cauliflowerr (broccoli may be used instead).
Cook 3 minutes.
Add tomato juice, mushrooms and seasoning and cook until tender.
Turn into casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese and cover dish.
Heat in 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour pineapple in Pyrex dish.
Put cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over this, then add in nuts. Melt butter and pour over all ingredients.
Cook for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: autumn tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use about 1 teaspoon of mix with boiling water.
Adjust to taste.

title: gourmet bean & veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except avocado, in saucepan. Heat over medium heat until cheese is melted; stir occasionally. Add avocado. Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
(Never freezes completely solid because of alcohol.)
Serve slush.
(Whiskey sour or wine glasses work well.)
Keep unused slush in freezer.
Serve with short cocktail straws.
Great pink color!

title: political roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Have roast at room temperature.
Make a mixture of all the spices and sugar.
Rub into the roast well. Place roast in a covered roasting pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off, but do not open the door.
Forty-five minutes before you plan to eat, uncover roast, turn oven back on and let roast cook for 45 minutes.

title: belgium salad
directions: Put together beans, corn, peas, pimento, celery, pepper, onion and cheese in large bowl.
Bring to a boil the sugar and vinegar and cool.
Then add oil, pepper and salt.
Add all this to bowl. Mix good and seal in airtight bowl.
Refrigerate.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: ice cream and cake
directions: Cut angel food cake into four, even horizontal slices.
Fill between layers with three choices of your favorite ice cream which have been allowed to soften slightly.

Strawberry on the bottom, vanilla in the middle, and chocolate on top make a nice arrangement. Frost cake with one pkg. of Dream Whip or Cool Whip tinted pink or any complimentary color. Return to freezer until ready to serve. Caution: the Dream Whip will dry out if prepared too far in advance. It is best to make it the day it is to be served. Store in loosely wrapped foil.

title: quick banana nut bread
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and bananas and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Turn out on rack and cool.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk until well blended.
Stir in crabmeat, Swiss cheese and chopped green onions to taste.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cook 4 minutes on High setting.
Add peanuts; cook 4 to 5 minutes on High setting. Mixture should be light brown.
Add vanilla and butter and mix well.
Cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in baking soda until mixture is foaming and light.
Pour on a greased baking sheet. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Empty all cereals, pretzels and nuts into a large kitchen trash bag (prefer white).
Mix.
Melt butter in saucepan and add Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Mix and add to dry ingredients; mix some more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Fry onions in oil until lightly brown.
Add salt, pepper, barbecue sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and sugar. Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring chicken, broth and water to a boil; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add carrots and onion.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer, until chicken is no longer pink near bone.
Remove skim off all fat.
Stir in noodles.
Increase heat; cook 8 to 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender. Tear meat into meat size bites.
Stir in.

title: giant cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 12-inch pizza pan. On sheet of waxed paper, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, brown sugar and egg for 2 minutes, until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture; beat just until combined.
Add 1/2 cup candies; mix well. Turn out dough onto pan.
With spatula, spread dough to edge of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, until brown; cool on rack.
Spread with icing and decorate with candies and syrup.

title: baked pork and dressing
directions: Place ham and dressing in baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add all dry ingredients together in bowl then add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine everything; cook until noodles are done to satisfaction.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Combine cheese and Worcestershire sauce; blend well.
Stir in 1/4 cup parsley and 1/2 cup pecans. Shape into large ball and roll in remaining pecans. Chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Grease a baking pan or cookie sheet.
Turn on a burner to medium.
Pour 2 cups of hot water into the bottom half of the boiler.
Put it on the hot burner.
Put the chocolate into the top of the boiler.
Slowly melt the chocolate over hot water.
Remove the top half of the boiler immediately when chocolate is melted. Stir the peanuts into the chocolate with a fork and mix well.
Use a spoon to pick up the peanut cluster and put it in the pan or cookie sheet.
After that, set the clusters aside to cool.

title: coconut cake filling
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan and boil.
Pour over beaten egg whites.
Mix well.
Add coconut and boil for 4 or 5 minutes. Spread on favorite cake layers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Put broccoli and onion in butter and cook 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions.
While this is cooking, melt the butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stir well; do not brown.
Add milk.
Stir constantly until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese begins to melt.
Mix drained macaroni and cheese sauce together.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: First cut biscuits into fourths and roll pieces in 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Kitchen shears work great for cutting biscuits.
Rub tube or Bundt pan with butter.
Place biscuits in pan.
Then place in saucepan to melt the butter, 1 1/3 cups sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Bread is not to be cut to serve, but is to be pulled apart.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger, turkey, chopped onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat mixture and heat.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, make layers as follows:
sauce mixture, noodles, sauce mixture, Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 cottage cheese.
Repeat layers above, finishing top layer with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top over mixture.
Pour 1/4 cup water in each corner of pan.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and brown cheese.
If using glass dish, reduce heat to 325°.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and sort
beans;
cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Let beans boil several minutes.
Remove from heat; cover. Let soak overnight.
Heat bean mixture to boiling; add remaining ingredients, except
ham and rice.	Cover and simmer 2 hours or until
beans
are
tender.	Add
more
water during cooking if necessary.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and walnuts.
Beat until cool.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cool!
Cut!
Eat!

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and slice bananas in medium pieces; slice the grapes in half and remove the seeds.
Then in a large bowl, mix the bananas and grapes together; then blend in the salad dressing.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup in 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 cans of water.
Add onion soup mix and rice.
Mix well. Put chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut each piece into 4 pieces lengthwise. Scrape away pulp carefully, leaving thin layer on skins.
Reserve pulp for other use.
Place potato skins in shallow dish.
Drizzle with butter and sprinkle evenly with cheese, bacon, salt and pepper.
Bake 15 minutes until cheese is melted and golden. Combine garlic chives, sour cream and horseradish.
Serve in a bowl to dip potatoes in.

title: lemon meringue cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until top springs back.
Immediately turn onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Peel off foil; beginning at narrow end, roll up cake with towel in jelly roll fashion.
Cool thoroughly.

title: apple and cheddar gratin
directions: In a well-buttered 1-quart shallow baking dish, arrange the apple slices and sprinkle them with the raisins, the cinnamon and the lemon juice.
In a small bowl, combine the sugar, the flour and the salt.
Blend in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal (I use the food processor for this) and toss the mixture with the Cheddar.

Sprinkle the Cheddar mixture over the apple mixture and bake the gratin in the upper third of a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until the apples are tender. Serve the gratin as a dessert or as an accompaniment to roast pork or ham.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no chop stir-fry(wok)
directions: Stir soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in water, sherry, bouillon granules and ginger.
Set aside.
Shape beef into 3/4-inch meatballs.
Add cooking oil; preheat wok over high heat. Stir-fry meatballs for 3 minutes or until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts and pea pods. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir soy mixture; add to wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Stir in peanuts.
Serve over chow mein noodles or hot, cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: All veggies are chopped or use food processor to chop.
Mix all ingredients together except flour. Cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours until onions are soft.
Use hot juice to mix flour into paste.
Add to relish and let thicken.
Yields about 6 pints.
Can and jar.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add soups, corn, pimento and sour cream.
Add noodles; stir all together.
Place in casserole dish. Spread bread crumbs over all.
Pour the melted butter over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 15 minutes.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Knead on surface, dusted with Bisquick.
Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise in warm place, about 30 minutes, or unti soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in casserole pan, spread evenly.
Pour in Veg-All. Mix broth, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom together.
Pour in pan.
For topping, mix flour, milk and butter together, blend well.
Pour evenly over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° or until browned.

title: heavenly chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 14-inch pan with cooked, chopped broccoli.
Cut up chicken that has been cooked.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
Sprinkle lemon pepper over chicken.
Mix chicken soup with juice and the mayonnaise and spread over chicken.
Layer cheese on the chicken.
Crush saltines and pour oil or butter over them; mix well.
Sprinkle crumbs over cheese. Bake about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: Mix condensed milk, whole milk, beaten eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
In a 1 pound coffee can, put 2 cups of mixture.
Place lid on firmly and tape.
Place 1 pound coffee can inside a 3 pound coffee can.
Put in 1/4 cup rock salt.
Add ice to 1/2 way up can. Add another 1/4 cup rock salt, then fill with ice to top.
Place lid on firmly and tape.
Kick the can back and forth for 15 minutes.
Check for freezing.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Sprinkle salt onto a flat bowl.
Mash garlic buds into salt with a fork.
Add in softened cream cheese, whipping with fork by hand.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill.
Yields about 1 quart.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time and cream well.
Add flour and cream alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Pour into a greased and floured 16 x 5-inch loaf cake pan or tube cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put in a cold oven.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef (keep out enough for top of cheese balls) and onion stems. Add to softened cream cheese. Form into 2 large balls. Roll in saved chopped dried beef and refrigerate until being used. Serve with crackers.

title: sugarless carrot pecan pie
directions: Combine oil and sweetener.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add half the flour mixture to oil mixture. Blend; add remaining flour mixture alternately with eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans alternately, mixing well to blend.
Pour into lightly oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken in salted water with grated ginger. When cool, cut into bite sizes. Mix dressing ingredients and refrigerate. Break lettuce into pieces. Chop onion tops.
Mix lettuce and onions, chicken bites and noodles. Dress just before serving.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cook pepper and onion in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soups, Rotel tomatoes and chicken, stirring until well blended. In a 13 X 9 X 2 pan.
Alternately layer tortillas, soup mixture and cheese; repeating for two layers.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and salt.
Blend well.
Add chicken broth, gizzard, liver and egg, if desired.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In small bowl, mix brown sugar, flour and walnuts.
Stir in melted oleo until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining gently into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon macaroni dinner
directions: Cook macaroni; drain. Do not rinse. Stir in soup and evaporated milk. Drain salmon, flake with a fork and add to macaroni with pimento and half of the cheese. Turn into a 6-cup casserole, arrange remaining cheese on top. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Puree bananas and mix all ingredients in a wide-mouthed container.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw in refrigerator for about 4 hours.
It will be mushy.
Add 2 liters chilled 7-Up.
Serves 50.

title: "philly" spinach dip
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Chill for 2 hours and serve.

title: butter icing
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Add milk and vanilla; beat until smooth, creamy and fluffy.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it is done.

title: beanies and wienies
directions: Remove pork from beans and heat.
Cut up hot dogs in bite size pieces.
Add to beans.
