Add the rest of ingredients.
Heat through and cook on low for 15 minutes.

title: nora's hot sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients in a dishpan until thick, approximately 45 minutes. Stir often, especially last few minutes.
Pour into hot, clean quart jars.
Allow to cool.

title: stuffed pasta
directions: Peel sausages; chop as fine as possible.
Press garlic.
Mix and saute until brown; drain.
Boil pasta shells; drain.
Thaw, drain and squeeze spinach.
Beat egg; combine with sausage and spinach.
Mix with hands.
Stuff into shells.
Place in casserole plate.
Cover with favorite red pasta sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano (approximately 2 teaspoons).
Cover with cheeses; bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan and place frozen rolls in pan. Mix brown sugar and pudding mix; sprinkle over rolls.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of other mixture.
Spread pecans on top of this and pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet overnight; do not cover.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let it stand for 10 minutes and turn out onto plate.

title: jerry's quiche lorraine
directions: Combine cheese with flour and place in pie crust.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard, then pour over cheese mixture.
Garnish, then bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 30 minutes.
I like to add 1/2 cup diced ham or crumbled bacon, sliced mushrooms and sliced olives.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel off outside eggplant and cut into wedges. Boil completely in salted water with pepper and little butter. When soft, drain and set aside.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break head of cauliflower into pieces
and dice.
Break up broccoli; dice and use tender parts of stems.
Use	some of the green
of the onions.
Drop frozen peas into boiling water and partially cook.
Mix all with mayonnaise and sour cream or yogurt, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift in allspice and flour.
Mix.
Stir in apples and raisins.
Put in 10 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: cheese twist bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with 1/2 teaspoon sugar, in a small bowl.
Heat butter and milk until lukewarm.
Place in a large bowl with remaining sugar and salt.
Mix egg in the dissolved yeast. Beat in 2 cups of flour and gradually beat in enough flour until a soft dough forms.
Knead soft dough until smooth and elastic. Cover and let rise in greased bowl until double its size.
This will take approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and roll into rectangle about 1/2 inch thick.
Sprinkle cheese into and roll tightly like a jelly roll.
Pinch seams and twist and place on greased sheet pan.
Let rise for 30 minutes and bake at 375° to 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: "guacamole dip"
directions: Mix all; keep covered in refrigerator until ready to serve with nacho chips.

title: granny's egg custard
directions: Beat well all ingredients except milk, then add milk and blend.
Pour into a greased and floured pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in one cup of water.
Boil remainder of water and sugar until dissolved.
Cool and add remaining ingredients; store in glass bottles.
Split the vanilla bean among the bottles.

title: raspberry and banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Add enough ice cubes to fill to 3-cup level.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 3 cups, 130 calories per cup.
Very nutritious during pregnancy (consult your physician).

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale, sherbet and ice just before serving.
Makes 30 punch cups.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
Spread 1/2 cup walnuts evenly on bottom of pan.
In heavy saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add butterscotch morsels.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in orange extract and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining walnuts on top and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes about 2 1/3 pounds.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Simmer beef with water, tomatoes, carrots, onion or leek, garlic, bay leaves, sugar and salt in kettle for 1 hour or until beef is tender.
Add cabbage, beans, corn, potatoes and parsley flakes.
Cook 45 minutes longer or until vegetables are done. Makes 12 cups.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
This recipe fills 4 one-pound coffee cans. Take out of freezer 3 or 4 hours before serving.
Add 4 large bottles ginger ale.
Serves 45 punch cups.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice thin and layer, lightly sprinkling each layer with salt.
Let stand at least 2 hours.
Combine equal parts of sugar and vinegar (enough to cover cucumbers when placed in a jar.)
Combine cucumbers, liquid, onion flakes and onion salt in jar.
Add liquid from cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: breakfast sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: saffron bread(saffransbrod)
directions: Mix yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Dry saffron in warm oven and pound smooth with small amount of sugar or dissolve in 1 tablespoon brandy.
Mix milk, saffron, sugar, salt, egg, butter and small amount of flour.
Add yeast and remaining flour; beat with wooden spoon until smooth and firm.
Sprinkle with flour; cover with clean towel and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
Turn out on floured baking board and knead until smooth.
Divide into portions and make braided loaves and/or buns in different shapes.
Place on buttered baking sheets; cover and let rise.
Brush with slightly beaten egg.
Sprinkle with almonds and coarse sugar; bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake buns in hot oven (425°) for 5 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In wok, saute onions, mushrooms, pea pods and broccoli in peanut oil.
After 5 minutes, add chicken and water chestnuts. Saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, chicken broth, ginger and cornstarch until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Bring vegetables to the sides of wok; pour in chicken broth mixture and let boil until thickened.
Stir vegetables into sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth; gradually blend in sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Spoon pie filling on top when serving.

title: brown stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes (save fat for frying).
Roll meat in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot fat.
Add onions and lightly brown.
Add water and simmer from 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, about 30 minutes longer. Thicken gravy with leftover flour.

title: easy rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until melted.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to shortening mixture.
Add egg and then flour.
Mix thoroughly. Cover with a damp cloth and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Knead; make out rolls and place on buttered pan.
Let rise for 2 hours before baking.
Brush with margarine and bake at 425° until browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil or applesauce, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until foamy.
Stir in zucchini; add crushed pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir gently until blended.
Divide into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch bread pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or until brown on edges).
Using the substitute eggs and applesauce causes it to get done in about 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and turn onto wire rack to cool completely.

title: party turnovers
directions: Brown ground beef; add soup and cheese.
Separate rolls.
Cut in two pieces.
Place small amount of filling on each roll.
Roll up.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients; mix well. Shape into six patties.
In a skillet, fry patties in margarine over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until heated through.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: pound cake with caramel frosting
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add the egg yolks, one at

a time, beating after each addition. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with half and half, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed until foamy. Gradually add remaining 2/3 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.

Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on a rack.
Frost with Easy Caramel Frosting and garnish with pecan halves, if desired.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Add 1/4 cup water and cornstarch; mix well.
Heat remaining water and lemon concentrate to boiling stage.
Lower heat; slowly add egg yolk mixture while stirring. Cook until thick and glossy.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and stir until well blended.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Place in a greased casserole. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: morocco carrot soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large heavy pot over medium-low heat.
Add the onion and ginger; cook until the onion is wilted, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the rice and curry powder.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring well.

title: broccoli hot dip(servings:  4)
directions: Melt butter and Cheez Whiz together until blended.
Add soup, mushrooms, onion and seasonings.
Mix well in saucepan.
Add broccoli or cauliflower.
Keep warm when serving with Dorito chips, etc.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water; add rest of ingredients and toss lightly.
Place in 10 x 6 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 2nd 1/2 cup of noodles (not mixed in) over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine milk, cream and sugar, stirring to dissolve sugar. Chill thoroughly.
Prepare juices and bananas.
Mix with milk mixture.
Place in electric freezer; freeze until firm.
Pack with ice and salt for several hours.

title: aunt francis' banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture in bottom of bowl to hold vanilla wafers.
Line bowl with wafers, sliced bananas and mixture.
Repeat.
Crush a few wafers to decorate top.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Drain fat and add salt, pepper, chili and water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Butter both sides of flour tortillas and lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Each shell should be folded in half and set side by side with open end up.
Fill each shell with the hot meat mixture and sprinkle some onions and cheese into each one.
Spoon remaining meat and onions and cheese over top of all of it.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza rushca(two crust italian pie)
directions: Prepare pie pastry per your recipe.
Line a large deep dish pie plate (I use a paella pan) and roll out a top crust.
Beat the eggs; stir in Ricotta cheese, onion, parsley, Parmesan cheese and season liberally with salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion, mushrooms and butter.
Break up broccoli in baking dish.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and hot rice.
Add to onion, mushrooms and butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients and place in
greased baking dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and spread on top of the first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Mix the sugar and eggs. Add the coconut, vanilla, dates and nuts. Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. While hot, stir with wooden spoon. Let cool. Make into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: seafood cakes
directions: Mix and add 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Shape into balls and roll in remainder of bread crumbs.
Flatten; refrigerate 30 minutes. Using oil, cook 5 minutes on each side.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up apples and bananas.
Mix all ingredients together and let set for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin orange poppy seed cake(easy, moist, tasty!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan. Combine cake mix, pumpkin, eggs and orange juice in large bowl. Beat at low speed until moistened. Beat on medium for 2 minutes. Add poppy seeds; mix until blended. Pour into pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Drizzle with glaze when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and celery until tender.
In large bowl, combine rice, celery and onion with other ingredients.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows, using double boiler.
Add color and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper to form a Christmas wreath.

title: barbecue sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook several hours in crockpot.

title: ruby breakfast sauce
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine pie filling, cranberry sauce, syrup, orange juice and butter. Microwave on High for 3 minutes; stir. Microwave 2 to 3 minutes longer or until butter is melted and mixture is heated through, stir. Serve over pancakes or French toast. Yield: 4 cups.

title: chocolate cream pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; add milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils; boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into individual dessert dishes.
Press plastic wrap directly onto surface of pudding.
Cool; chill until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger biscuit casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except cheese and biscuits.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top this with 1 can of biscuits.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Use only the tops of the broccoli.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Melt Cheez Whiz and pour over broccoli.
Put a bit of water in it; sprinkle with chow mein noodles or triskets.
Place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: perfect chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour, then add milk. Boil slowly until thick.
Cool mixture before adding beaten egg yolk. Boil again until thick as desired and add pinch of salt and vanilla.
Pour into cooled pie crust.

title: coleslaw crunch salad
directions: Dressing: In medium bowl, whisk together the oil, sugar, vinegar and the seasoning packets from the Ramen noodles. Set aside.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Put layer of asparagus in Pyrex dish and add layer of soup, then layer of crushed Ritz crackers.
Add butter, salt and pepper. Then add another layer of asparagus and soup.
Top with layer of crackers and bake in moderate oven, about 45 minutes, until brown on top.

title: rhubarb cream pie(1964 cookbook)
directions: Blend sugar,
flour,
nutmeg
and butter.
Add eggs and beat smooth. Pour
over rhubarb in pastry-lined pan.
Top with lattice-style pastry.
Bake
in
hot
oven at 450° for 15 minutes; then in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until custard bubbles up and fruit is tender.

title: cumberland mountain pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and milk all together and add flavoring.
Beat up real good.
Pour this in a lined pie pan and bake in slow oven.
After it is done, take out and cool.
Add a meringue made with 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons of sugar. Spread on the pie and bake in a slow oven until nicely brown.

title: cheddar nachos
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Place half of the tortilla chips in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with half the shredded cheese and top with half the jalapeno pepper slices.
Broil until cheese melts and chips are lightly browned.
Remove nachos to platter.
Repeat remaining chips, cheese and pepper slices. Serves 4.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Mix ice cream
mix
according
to
directions.	Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into the ice cream cones (the flat bottomed ones) and place on a
cookie sheet and bake for 30 or 40 minutes or until browned.

title: pretty pink punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour Sprite in slowly and stir. Vary the color and flavor by using another flavor of sherbet.

title: cranberry sherbert
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Cook cranberries in boiling water until soft, then force through a strainer.
Add soaked gelatin, sugar, and lemon juice and freeze.
A delicious treat to roast turkey.

title: zucchini velvet soup
directions: Cut up and boil squash and onions for 30 minutes in broth.
Put in blender to make a puree.
Add in blender cream cheese and half and half or milk.
Put small amounts in blender.
Season with curry powder to taste.
Heat and serve hot.
Can be halved or use 1/3 of recipe.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.
Serve 1 slice of zucchini on top.
This is served without crackers or bread.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add Ro-Tel, soup, corn, Minute rice and Velveeta cheese. Let Velveeta cheese melt, stirring occasionally. Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top has melted.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a medium size casserole dish with nonstick coating. In a large bowl, stir together the sugar and flour. Gradually stir in cheese. Add the drained pineapple chunks. Stir until ingredients are well combined. Pour into the prepared casserole dish.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Mix all together; bring to boil over high heat. Boil 18 minutes on medium-low heat, stirring occasionally. Put pan in cold water and beat for about 5 to 7 minutes until it thickens. Pour into buttered plate or pan. Cut when cooled. If it hardens too soon, just add a little milk to smooth it out, then put in dish. Can also be used for icing on a jam cake.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well with sweet milk.
Have dough stiff.
Cook in deep oil, slow.

title: rice-a-roni casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Add vegeburger and cook until brown.
Layer string beans, then cheese, chiles, sour cream and then rice mix alternately.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix ingredients and leave, uncovered, on kitchen counter for 3 days, stirring occasionally with a plastic or wooden spoon. Starter does not rise, only bubbles.
Place in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days and feed with the following at least twice before using Starter to make bread.
After starting to make bread, feed every 3 to 5 days.
Will last a long time.

title: kielbasa
directions: Place crescent rolls together into long strips.
Spread with spicy mustard.
Roll around kielbasa.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and slice.
Serve warm.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and slice into 2 inch wedges.
Arrange potatoes in a 9 x 13 inch greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; cook until it comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Baste with syrup.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
If tomatoes are still lumpy, use electric mixer for about 1 minute. Pour into jars and seal.

title: one pan potato and chicken teriyaki
directions: While potatoes cook in large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add onions and teriyaki sauce.
Toss until heated thoroughly.
Time:
20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions or onion salt.
Drain fat.
Add 1 can tomato soup and green beans.
Stir until mixed together on medium heat.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Prepare 4 to 6 servings of mashed potatoes.

title: chicken winglets
directions: Mix batter by combining milk, flour, soy sauce, eggs and salt (to taste); mix until smooth.
Dip winglets in batter; fry in deep hot fat (350°) until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese with sugar until creamy.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange strawberries on filling and top with jelly.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: veggie bars(club member:  terah)
directions: Unroll crescent rolls. Place in lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, pressing edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan. Bake 7 to 8 minutes until brown at 350°; cool. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix. Beat until smooth. Spread over crust. Combine peppers and remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over cream cheese mixture. Cover and chill 8 hours. Cut into squares.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: pink fruit
directions: Drain fruits and pineapple, then mix all together. Put into bowl and cover, then refrigerate.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans (save some to lay on top).
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: o' henry's
directions: Blend Karo syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and Special K.
Stir fast to mix. Spread in a jelly roll pan while warm.

title: ground beef steak supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup and water.
Roll mixed meat on a floured board.
Make into patties.
Brown in hot oil on both sides.
Place in a covered dish and add hot oil.
Mix can of soup and can of water together.
Pour over meat mixture and bake at 300° for 2 hours, covered.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine beef and ham with milk, eggs, onion, bread crumbs, salt, allspice and pepper. Shape into meatballs about 2 inches in diameter. Carefully arrange meatballs in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.

Turn control to high. Stir in flour that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water. Add catsup and dill weed. Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly thickened. Turn heat off. Stir in sour cream.

title: fried rabbit or squirrel
directions: Clean rabbit, parboil, then coat with flour, salt and pepper and place in skillet of hot oil.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the last 6
ingredients well and pour over carrots, onions and bell peppers and marinate several hours or overnight.

title: hot egg nog
directions: Cream egg yolks and sugar until light in color.
Heat milk to boiling point and add a little to the creamed mixture, stirring. Gradually blend creamed mixture into pot of milk, stirring constantly.
Fold beaten egg whites into milk and creamed mixture. Add desired amount of rum extract and serve with nutmeg sprinkled on top.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together, adding nuts last.
Spread in a large jelly roll pan (15 x 11 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg together.
Add dry ingredients. Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tucson dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl at low speed, beat cream cheese and sour cream until well blended and smooth.
Rinse dried beef and pat dry.
Chop coarsely.
Gently stir dried beef, green chilies and onion into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into a shallow 2-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle chives and pecans on top. Bake for 20 minutes or until puffed and edges are bubbly.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
You can hardly make enough of this for a cocktail party, it goes so fast.
The recipe doubles easily.

title: coconut cake
directions: Separate eggs and set aside whites for frosting. Cream sugar, shortening and egg yolks. Add milk and dry ingredients slowly, beating about 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool when done.

title: chocolate cake(with coffee instead of milk)
directions: Cook together for 5 minutes the first 3 ingredients.
Let mixture cool. While mixture cools, cream the butter and 1 cup sugar together.
Add eggs. Add cold coffee alternately with flour, which has been sifted together with soda, baking powder and salt. Add the cooked mixture of sugar, coffee and cocoa last.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Cake will stay moist for several days.
Use a buttercream icing.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Debone chicken breasts, then split in halves.
Top each with 1/2 slice Swiss cheese.
Add slices of ham to each.
Place generous dollop of cream cheese in the center of each; roll up. Wrap slice of bacon around rolls; secure with a toothpick.
Place in a flat baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from pan; place on serving plate.
Add mushrooms to juice in pan; pour over chicken.
Garnish with parsley.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Beat egg with water in shallow bowl.
Place crumbs on another sheet of waxed paper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture, then egg, then crumbs. Heat oil over medium heat and fry chicken 4 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add oil. Mix. Add eggs, mixing in one at a time. Stir in pecans. Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour or can be baked in small loaf pans during the holidays for gift giving. Moister if frozen for a day or two.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. In medium bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut in squares.
Makes approximately 3 dozen brownies.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Cook very slowly in heavy saucepan milk and sugar and continue to stir.
Add 4 tablespoons flour mixed in about 1 cup of milk. Add salt and beat eggs and add to mixture.
Cook slowly and stir until custard is thickened.
I like to refrigerate overnight but may use same day.
Before pouring custard in freezer, add vanilla and additional sugar until custard is over sweet.
You may add fresh or canned fruit to same vanilla custard.
Add can milk if custard does not come to line mark in freezer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs well and mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Blend together well. Form 3 or 4 rolls. Roll in paprika and then in finely chopped pecans. Wrap each roll in waxed paper or foil and store in refrigerator. Serve with crackers.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Pour all ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch pan. No pan preparation is necessary. Mix well with fork; smooth batter out. Wipe sides of pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Nothing could be easier - and it's delightful served cold with Cool Whip.

title: hoosier persimmon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk, 2 cups sugar, salt and pulp.
Mix well.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients for topping; pour over pie.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake for 10 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon slices.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole and lay bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture thickens and bacon is brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix sugar with berries.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 of the 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Then beat until smooth.
Slice angel food cake into thin slices.
Arrange slices from one cake to cover entire pan.
Top with cheese mixture.
Arrange slices from second cake.
(Drizzle Triple Sec or sherry over cake; optional.)
Top with berries and remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Brown chicken in electric skillet.
Add green pepper and onion.
A few minutes later, add mushroom soup and milk.
Simmer until gravy reaches desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice.

title: frozen fluffy strawberry pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up side to rim of 9-inch pie plate.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in pureed strawberries and ReaLemon brand.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust (mixture should mound slightly).
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook
rice
minutes
in
4 cups water with bouillon cubes. Drain
rice.
Add
all ingredients, except liquid from artichokes.
Add liquid last.
Mix well and chill.
Serve cold as a salad in tomato cups or as a side dish.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine shrimp with all ingredients in a shallow bowl. Marinate in fridge for several hours.
Remove shrimp from marinade and place in shallow baking pan.
Broil 8-inches from heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn 1 time and place in serving bowl.

title: sweet 'n sour beef
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and liquids.
Cook until it boils and thickens.
Add pineapple, green peppers, tomatoes and beef.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except apples.
Add apples and mix until evenly coated; put in crust.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 450° approximately 45 minutes or until nearly dry.

title: pork chops and tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat chops with flour and place them in baking pan. Do not layer chops. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste. Cook in oven for 30 minutes, turning once. Add onions and tomatoes. Cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: venison burger
directions: Combine meat with seasonings and mix well.
Add egg and condensed milk.
Add enough bread crumbs to make mixture hold together without being sticky or dry.
Season to your liking. Shape into 6 medium patties and broil, fry or charcoal grill as you would hamburgers.
Top with sliced cheese in the last minute of cooking, if you prefer.
Serve on toasted sesame buns with your favorite additions to round out a different and highly satisfying meal.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in buttered oven to table, 13 x 9-inch dish. Mix butter and oil.
Brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf with creamed peas
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch loaf pan, which has been greased and floured, with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: In
large bowl mix all ingredients.
Beat on high speed with an	electric beater. Beat for 3 minutes.
Place batter in funnel pan
which has been greased with Crisco and dusted with flour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tester (or toothpicks) comes out clean.
Ice if desired.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk as directed; set aside.
Crush cookies in food processor or blender.
Set aside.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix pudding mixture together with margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar mixture and add Cool Whip.
Layer in container beginning with pudding mixture, then crushed cookie layer, etc.
Be sure to end with layer of crushed cookies covering the top.
Place a few "gummy worms" around the top and add a few stems of silk flowers into the pudding.
When finished, it should look like a potted plant.

title: sand tarts
directions: Put shortening in large bowl.
Add sugar.
Mix together.
Add eggs.
Measure dry ingredients on piece of wax paper (flour, baking soda, powder and salt).
Take 6 or 7 heaping tablespoonfuls of dry mixture.
Add to sugar mixture, then add 1/8 cup of milk.
Mix with spoon.
Do same with flour (three different times with flour, two different times with milk).
Get in with hands.
Divide into three balls.
Roll up in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Heat butter and sugar in a small saucepan until butter is just melted.
Cool.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until frothy.
Add vinegar, vanilla and butter/sugar mixture.
Mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 cheese and mix with soup and milk.
Layer broccoli, melted cheese mix and chunks of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with a layer of croutons.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Fill pie shell with crabmeat and cheese, reserving a few pieces of crab for garnish.
Combine eggs, cream, wine, onion and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 40 minutes.
Garnish with reserved crabmeat.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Place roast in crock-pot and cook on low for 8 hours.
Remove roast and drain liquid.
Cut up roast into small pieces and return to crock-pot on low.
Add barbecue sauce to roast and cook for 1 more hour.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve on buns.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onions and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Pour off grease.
Add water and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper, then add parsley. Heat to serve, but do not boil.

title: raisin jumbles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add raisins and date mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno rice eliminator
directions: In small saucepan, bring water, bouillon and salt to boil.
In heavy saucepan, saute onions in oil until soft.
Add rice, stirring until brown.
Add boiling bouillon stock to rice, cheese and jalapenos.
Mix. Simmer about 45 minutes or until rice is soft.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Brown pork chops; sprinkle with salt.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Slice apples; arrange on top of chops.
Sprinkle sugar on top of apples.
Put flour in chop drippings; stir constantly.
Add water as needed.
Add vinegar, salt and raisins to sauce, then pour sauce over chops and apples.
Cover; cook at 400° for 30 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt together; beat until foamy.
Add scalded milk and vanilla; beat well.
Bake pie crust 5 minutes at 450° before adding the filling.
Add filling and bake 5 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg with large spoon.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs with electric mixer; pour over cake mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams.
Reserve 1/4 cup of liquid.
Combine clams, reserved liquid and all other ingredients, mixing well until blended.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients (best to put in blender).
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring often.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Reserve 1/3 of the mixture.
To 2/3 of the mixture add chicken, olives, chilies and 1/2 of the cheese.
On a baking sheet, fill the tortillas with the mixture and fold over.
Spread the remaining soup and sour cream mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Add the remaining
ingredients
the
next
morning.
Line 3 empty coffee cans with wax paper.
Divide batter into 3 cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Turn out of cans. Allow to cool.

title: frying pan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients except chili powder in large bowl.
Add green pepper, onion and cheese.
In heavy skillet heat oil and mix in chili powder.
Cool, add milk and eggs.
Stir into dry mixture until well blended.
Return to skillet and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve hot.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Let stand in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, oil, eggs and corn.
Beat. Stir in peppers and onions.
Pour half of batter into greased pan. Sprinkle with half of cheese.
Cover with remaining batter.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° to 400° (8 to 10-inch pan).

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together and spread on large plate or platter.
Place lettuce over mixture.
Spread meat over lettuce.
Place onions over lettuce.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Chill until ready to serve.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and margarine; press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese with 1 cup 10x sugar.
Fold in one container of La Creme and spread mixture over cooled crust.
Prepare pudding with just 3 cups of milk, adding lemon rind.
Spoon this over the cheese layer.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook together over medium heat the pineapple juice, sugar, egg, flour and vinegar until it makes a pudding-like consistency. Leave in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, stir in the chunk pineapple, marshmallows, apples, peanuts and Cool Whip.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Take 1 roll and cut into 4 triangles.
Roll smokie starting at large end, overlapping to seal.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sour cream cucumber soup
directions: Pare and slice 2 cucumbers (about 3 cups).
Cook with onions in butter until soft.
Stir in flour; add broth slowly.
Cover; simmer until cucumbers are tender, about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; add seasoned salt.
Whirl smooth in blender or processor.
Chill well. Pare remaining cucumber and scoop out seeds.
Grate the cucumber medium coarse.
Add to chilled soup base along with sour cream. Blend in lemon juice and dill.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice very thin the cucumbers.
Cover with salt; stir in.
Set for 3 hours.

title: karon vaughn's mostaccioli dish
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion powders and drain.
Add Ragu and heat.
Prepare noodles according to package and add to meat mixture.
Place in 9 x 13 dish and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Place butter in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Heat butter until melted.
Tilt dish to coat with butter.
Pour toast over butter. Sprinkle cheese on toast and set aside.

title: okra balls
directions: Place egg, Bisquick and salt into a bowl and add enough milk to make a thick batter.
Add okra and stir well.
The mixture should be thick enough to drop; if not, add a little more Bisquick.
Drop by tablespoon into medium grease.
When one side is nicely browned, turn and cook the other side.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Cut the squash lengthwise, then crosswise into bite-size pieces.
Heat oil to medium in nonstick pan.
Quickly saute squash about 1 minute with basil.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick cartilage from meat; combine with all other ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Thoroughly blend.
Form into burger-size patties.
Cakes should be tightly formed so not to fall apart. Wrap in waxed paper; chill until ready to use.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake clean potatoes until done.
Cut in half and cool. (Baking potatoes work best.)
Dip out potato, leaving a shell. Cream scooped out potato with salt, pepper, butter, milk and grated cheese to taste.
Spoon back into shell; sprinkle top with more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and potato is hot through.
Serve hot.

title: chicken kiev
directions: To prepare the herbed butter mix in a medium bowl the softened butter, parsley, tarragon, chives, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into a rope for easy cutting.
Wrap in aluminum foil and freeze until firm.
Next prepare the chicken rolls by cutting chicken breasts into halves.
Place them between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and pound until 1/4 inch thick.
Work very carefully, not tearing the meat.
Cut the frozen butter into 16 pieces.
Place 1 piece herbed butter on center of each chicken breast.
Fold chicken over butter, making sure, the butter is enclosed.
Fasten chicken rolls with wooden picks.
Roll chicken into flour, dip into beaten eggs, coat completely with bread crumbs.
Repeat with every chicken roll. Cover the breaded chicken rolls and refrigerate them about 2 hours. Heat oil in Dutch oven (4 inches oil) to 360°F.
Fry two pieces at a time, for about 8 minutes, until deep golden brown, turning if necessary.
Drain on paper towel.

title: killed onions
directions: Slice
enough onions to fill a 1-quart bowl.
Add salt. Heat bacon drippings, vinegar and water to a boil.
Pour over onions and cover.
Let set 15 minutes and serve.

title: apricot delight
directions: Warm pineapple.
Add sugar, Jell-O and mashed cream cheese. Refrigerate until mixture begins to jell.
Fold in Dream Whip (made to package directions) and baby food.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: "chestnut burrs"
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet. Add chopped onion, chopped celery, parsley, salt and pepper. Saut. Stir in bread cubes. Mix ground beef, eggs, salt and pepper. Shape into balls (about 3-inches); flatten into thin patties. Fill with stuffing mixture and shape back into large ball, leaving top open. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease one 2 quart casserole dish and set aside.
Combine the butternut squash, white sugar, brown sugar, margarine, pineapple, cinnamon, vanilla, and nutmeg.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake for 40-45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fun and easy mints
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar, flavoring and coloring; mix.
When mixed into ball, knead like dough for several minutes.
Pinch small piece and roll into size of marble.
Roll in sugar and push into mold.
Unmold onto wax paper and let dry for 1 hour.
Best to let age for several days.
Can be frozen in a sealed container.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix together in one bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. When cool, spread with one can chocolate fudge frosting.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Take meat from bone.
Tear into bite size pieces. Put into baking dish.
Mix soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine. Add milk. Gradually add flour, mixing until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples and cut into thick slices.
Mix half the sugar with the cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Blend the flour, remaining sugar and the butter and work into small crumbs.
Sprinkle the crumbs over the apples. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes more.

title: mary's cake(dietetic)
directions: Blend margarine, eggs, sweetener, vanilla, flour, soda and spices.
Add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in mixing bowl and blend well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 1/2-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Combine 4 tablespoons peach Schnapps, 2 tablespoons orange juice and confectioners sugar.
While cake is still warm in pan, poke holes in cake.
Pour liqueur mixture over.
Allow cake to cool in pan at least 2 hours before removing.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Combine all and mix well.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger; drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for several hours or until beans are good and tender.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Melt butter in small skillet; add onion and pimento.
Saute until onion is tender.
Combine macaroni, onion, mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon in lightly buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey spaghetti bake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Mix ingredients and spread in Pyrex.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add soups, sauce and peppers. Layer Doritos, meat mixture and cheese in casserole dish, ending with cheese.
Brown in 300° oven until cheese melts (30 minutes).

title: sour cream
directions: Place in blender and blend until smooth.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Fill paper baking cups in muffin pans 2/3 full.
Cream the cheese with the sugar, beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture in each cupcake.
Bake as package directs for cupcakes.
Makes about 30 cupcakes.

title: cromer's catfish stew
directions: Slice fatback into 1/4-inch slices.
Remove rind and dice into small cubes.
Fry fatback until it begins to float.
Peel onions and dice into small pieces.
Place onions in the fatback grease and cook until well done.
Pour in one quart of clamato juice and 1 quart of ketchup.
Rinse bottles with water and add to the mixture (about 2 quarts water).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the fish fillets and let them cook until well done.
Cover pot and simmer to thicken to desired consistency.
Serve over rice or loaf of bread with slaw or pickles.

title: cheesy broccoli pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 2 baking sheets. Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain well. In a medium skillet, heat oil over low heat. Add garlic. Saute for 2 minutes. Add broccoli. Cook, stirring, until moisture has evaporated, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool slightly. In a medium bowl, combine broccoli mix, Mozzarella, Parmesan, roasted peppers, oregano, salt and pepper. Mix well. On a lightly floured surface, divide dough into 8 pieces. Roll out each piece to form a 6-inch circle. Spoon an equal amount of broccoli mix in the center of each circle. Fold dough over filling to form a half circle. Press edges with a fork to seal; prick a few holes in pocket top. Place pockets on prepared baking sheet. Bake 25 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and add butter.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Pour 1/2 jar Prego over spaghetti and top with Swiss cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle ground beef over that and top with pepperoni.
Pour the other 1/2 Prego over the meat. Top with the remaining 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle a little oregano over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cinnamon sherry toddy
directions: Mix eggnog, sherry and powdered cinnamon; beat well.
Stir in milk and salt; heat gently to below boiling.
Beat egg white to soft peaks; fold into hot nog.
Serve with cinnamon sticks for stirring.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan and cut into squares or bars.

title: lunch box cake(good for kids to try)
directions: Pour all ingredients into mixer bowl; blend at low speed until all is mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frosting is not necessary.

title: good baked beans
directions: Put in a large
pan and cook for 4 to 5 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with catsup and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Place in buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.
Place topping on meat loaf.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients except for the bacon.
Pour in a long glass casserole.
Place small strips of bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Beat together brown sugar, oil and egg.
Mix baking soda, salt, vanilla and sour milk.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour, rhubarb and nuts.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Sift together flour and sugar, pour boiled mixture over.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in greased and floured 13 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: piggy wraps
directions: Cut sausage into desired shapes.
Wrap in dough.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until golden brown. May be frozen.

title: coconut sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating one minute after each egg.
Add flour and soda, alternate with sour cream.
Add flavoring and mix well. Add coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan which has been greased and floured.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add salt to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble, fry and drain pork sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Mix well.
Into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan, lay the bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions and break into pieces. Layer in punch bowl as follows:
cake pieces, 3 to 4 Tbsp. pie filling, 3 to 4 Tbsp. pineapple, 3 to 4 Tbsp. Cool Whip, 3/4 Tbsp. pecan pieces.
Repeat layers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: anyberry upside-down cake
directions: Mix sugar into berries in bowl and let sit while you make the cake.
Make cake as described on package.
In a large flat pan, spread out the berries.
Pour the cake mix over the top and bake at temperature on package.

title: french quarter steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper; dredge meat, saving excess flour mixture.
Saute onions and peppers in hot oil; remove and drain.
Brown steak in remaining oil.
Add all other ingredients, including remaining flour.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: cajun special
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Combine flour, black pepper, red pepper, garlic and salt.
The flour should look fairly red.
Roll chicken in flour and fry in oil and butter.
When cooked, remove chicken and debone.
Remove all but 2 to 3 tablespoons of the remaining oil.
Leave all the blackened flour and chicken in the pan.
Saute onion and green pepper in pan until onions are clear.
Combine shredded chicken, vegetables, rice, chicken broth and sliced sausage into a kettle and simmer.
Adjust the flavor with cayenne pepper and black pepper.
Ten minutes before you serve, add the tomato wedges.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook pie crusts as indicated and cool.
Mix together coconut, margarine and pecans.
Brown in oven, then cool.
Beat together cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, icing and Cool Whip.
Layer in pie crust and top with cooled coconut and pecan mixture.
Freeze until 1 hour before serving.

title: sushi-fletcher
directions: Chop fish finely and marinate in vinegar for 40 to 50 minutes. Drain and press vinegar out or squeeze with hands.
Combine with mayonnaise, mustard and relish.
Season to taste with garlic, salt and pepper.
Serve on Ritz crackers with a drop of Tabasco sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first five ingredients together until creamy. Line large dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Cover with pudding mixture and continue layering until dish is full.
Garnish with wafers or Cool Whip.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside. Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and water; beat until creamy, then add eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes; let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: diana's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt. In small saucepan, bring butter and water to a boil; stir into sugar mixture.
Whisk in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan (batter will be thin).
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost while warm.
Let cool, then cut into 24 pieces.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake yellow cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Split in half lengthwise.
Mix 5 tablespoons flour and milk in saucepan.
Heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix sugar, salt, Crisco, margarine and vanilla.
Mix until fluffy. Add cooled milk mixture.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add food coloring.
Put filling on 1 half of cake.
Put the other half on top.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: grannie thurston's gingersnaps
directions: Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
(Cookies will firm quickly as they cool.)

title: beef taco bake
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, salsa, milk, tortillas and half the cheese.
Spoon into 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 4.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans, soak overnight.
Cook one hour.
Add all other ingredients except sausage and cook until beans are tender.
Add sausage 30 minutes before done.
Serve over rice.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve peach gelatin in boiling water; stir until dissolved. Add 3/4 cup cold water and mix well.
Chill until the consistency of an unbeaten egg white.
Stir in sliced peaches and banana. Pour into a lightly oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Soften gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Scald half-and-half cream and stir into gelatin mixture.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add whipping cream, sugar, and pureed peaches; mix well.
Add to gelatin mixture and stir well.
Pour over peach and banana layer. Chill at least 8 hours, or until firm.
Yield:
10-12 servings.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place eggs in buttered casserole.
Cook sausage and drain. Sprinkle sausage over eggs.
Pour sour cream over top and mix. Combine crumbs and cheese and sprinkle over casserole.
Place in a 350° oven; bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Serves 5.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Boil potatoes (sliced) and onions for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Stir in rest of ingredients until sauce thickens over medium heat.
Layer potatoes and sauce over ham in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and shortening with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after that.
Add flour with 7-Up soda and flavorings.
Cook 1 hour.

title: red-hot beef kabobs(with yogurt sauce)
directions: Trim fat from boneless beef sirloin steak.
Cut steak into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, oil, chili powder, salt and hot pepper sauce in medium bowl.
Add beef pieces; toss to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place layer of chicken on top.
Combine next three ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Spread cheese. Combine stuffing with butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Place crushed cookies in pie plate.
Melt oleo and pour over cookies, mix with fork and pat down.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package and pour over cookies.
Then put a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped pecans.

title: mexicali bean spread
directions: In a food processor or blender mix all ingredients together for about 1 minute or until smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Mix together eggs, milk and salt.
Stir into hot drained noodles and mix.
Add shredded sharp cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased 8 x 8-inch square pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bean macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, undrained bean salad, celery and egg.
Mix with French dressing, relish, salt, hot pepper sauce and pepper. Chill about one hour.
Garnish with hard cooked egg.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: super easy melt in your mouth panic dump dessert
directions: Match a cake mix with a pie filling.
Dump cake mix (dry) into bowl.
Dump melted butter over it as you stir with a fork.
Should be crumbly not gobby.
Dump 1/2 of this into 2 buttered pans, 9 x 13-inch.
Pat down.
Put fruit filling on top and then sprinkle remainder of cake mix on top.
You may add chips or coconut, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in salted water with butter. Cut chicken into bite size pieces if desired. Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder together. Add broccoli and chicken to soup mixture and pour into a large casserole dish.
Top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: lane cake(aunt tera's from theo brown)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, at moderate speed.
Makes a pound cake or 2 or 3 layers.
Bake at 350° (45 minutes for pound cake).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken or pork
directions: Cut chicken or pork into 1/2-inch pieces and brown in oil. Reduce heat; add onion.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer. Serve with rice if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chasu(chinese roast pork loin)
directions: Cut pork roast into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Add other ingredients together.
Marinate in sauce for 2 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Baste frequently.
Let stand a few minutes before slicing into smaller pieces.
Arrange beautifully in a plate.
Pour over just a little more sauce.
Serve with hot mustard, if preferred.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Boil the oleo, cocoa and water.
Add to dry mixture.
Add buttermilk, slightly beaten eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat and pour in sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut crunch cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cake mix, peanut butter and brown sugar on low speed until crumbly. Set aside 1/2 cup. Add water, eggs and oil to remaining crumb mix and blend on low until moistened. Beat on high for 2 minutes. Stir in 1/4 cup each of chocolate and peanut butter chips. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: quick sweet pickles
directions: Wash and drain pickles; soak for 20 or 25 minutes in cold water.
Drain well; slice in thick slices and add sugar, vinegar and cinnamon sticks.
Let stand until sugar dissolves; stir often. Pack back in jars and pour syrup back on pickles.
Refrigerate. These are real crisp.

title: the velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes; then sprinkle 1/2 cup on bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside remaining almonds and chocolate chips.
Measure remaining ingredients into mixer bowl.
Blend; then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chips and almonds.
Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on rack.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 14-inch buttered casserole.
Top with 2 1/2 cups corn flake crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: lobster thermidor afrikaans
directions: Drop frozen lobster tails into the boiling water (salted) and cover.
When the water boils again, lower the heat, boil gently for 11 minutes.
Drain; douse with cold water.
With scissors, cut lengthwise down each side of the membrane covering the meat.
Pull out the meat, chill and dice.
Wash the shells.
Saute the mushrooms in butter for 2 minutes; add the flour and seasonings. Stir in the milk and cream; cook slowly until thickened, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add the diced meat and sherry.
Refill the shells, brush with butter and egg.
Brown lightly in hot oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: streusel sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole dish.
Cook potatoes in water to cover 20 to 30 minutes or until firm and tender.
Drain and cool under cold water.
Slice in 1/2-inch thick rounds.
In prepared dish, arrange rounds in concentric circles, overlapping slices slightly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form mixture into one inch balls. Place on baking pan and bake at 350 degrees for approx. 20 minutes.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in two-quart casserole.
Add the onion and green pepper.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes; stir and microwave on High for another 4 minutes or until meat is browned.
Drain and stir in the remaining ingredients. Re-cover casserole dish.
Microwave on Medium-high for 22 minutes. Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Before serving, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate cookies like candy
directions: Children can make them with little help.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Sift the flour, baking soda, salt and spices together and blend thoroughly; set aside. Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until fluffy. Add eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition. Add a mixture of molasses and boiling water gradually, mixing well. Beating only until smooth after each addition, alternately add dry ingredients in fourths and sour milk in thirds to creamed mixture. Turn batter into a well-greased (bottom only) 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until gingerbread tests done. Cool in pan on wire rack. Makes one 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: cooked white icing
directions: Cook milk, flour and salt until thick (like gravy).
Stir while cooling.
Cream sugar, shortening, oleo and vanilla; then beat until turns snow white.
Add cooked and cooled mixture and beat.
Cannot overbeat.
Nice fluffy icing.
Goes with Red Velvet Cake.
I use on angel food cake.
Holds good.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix in order given well with a fork.
Knead on board; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet until lightly browned.

title: coon hunters cake
directions: Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Punch holes in cake and frost while warm.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mayonnaise.
Reserve nuts to roll log.
Roll in waxed paper to form log.
Roll log in chopped nuts before serving. Place log on serving dish surrounded by crackers for serving.
This makes an excellent party dish.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients and baste chops.
Place in baking dish and cover completely.
Bake at 230° until tender.

title: cough syrup
directions: Boil lemons until soft.
Slice into pan containing honey and camphor oil.
Cook slowly, until syrupy.
Take by spoonfuls for cough.

title: best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa and sugar together.
Add butter mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yield: 16 brownies.

title: beef rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Stir in rice, water, salt and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook on low heat until water is absorbed, 25 minutes.
Stir in cheese until it softens.
Combine tomato sauce and chili powder.
Pour over rice mixture.
Cover and heat 5 minutes, until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, vinegar and water.
Work pastry until pliable.
Yields 1 double crust pie.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, sifting soda with flour.
If using sweet milk, reduce soda to 1/4 teaspoon.
Bake in cake pan or muffin pan at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: killer brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, butter, nuts and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix by hand and spread 1/2 dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips and margarine with Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows and nuts.
Stir into chocolate mixture. Spread in foil lined 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan.
Peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 3/4 pounds.

title: butterscotch spoonoodles
directions: Combine noodles and nuts in a bowl.
Set aside.
Combine honey, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt in saucepan and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch morsels and stir until melted.
Pour over noodles and nuts; mix gently until coated.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let stand until set, or chill until firm.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Parboil peeled and sliced potatoes in salt water 15 minutes. Reserve 1 cup of potato liquid.
Place drained potatoes in crock-pot.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Separate biscuits into 3 sections and spread mixture on top.
Place a water chestnut on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Elegant!

title: grandma's rolls(makes crescent rolls or cinnamon rolls)
directions: In large bowl, combine shortening, salt, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup (1 stick) butter or margarine.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture and stir until blended.
In small bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar over 1/2 cup warm water (105° to 115°); stir to mix slightly.
Let rest 5 minutes.
To mixture in large bowl, add flour, eggs, yeast mixture and 1 cup cold water, stirring to mix well.
Dough will be sticky.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap or lid; refrigerate 5 hours or overnight.

title: fried squash or eggplant
directions: Use 2 medium yellow summer squash or zucchini or medium eggplant.
Cut squash or zucchini into 1/4 inch slices.
Place in plastic bag.
Add the Italian dressing and shake to coat thoroughly.

In a separate bag place the cheese and bread crumbs. Add the coated vegetable slices, close bag and shake to coat. Using a nonstick pan sprayed with cooking spray, add the vegetables in a single layer.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 5 to 7 minutes, just until tender and crisp.
If using eggplant, slice into 3/4 inch thick slices.
Moisten with the Italian dressing and roll in the cheese bread crumb mixture.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes at 475°, turn and bake other side for another 5 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 3 g, fat 3 g, calories 61.

title: tea cakes, old fashioned
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out enough at a time to fill the cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: gingerbread dancers
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and butter cookie sheets.
Heat the molasses to boiling point.
Add sugar, butter or shortening and milk.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Add to the first mixture; blend well.
Add a few tablespoons of water, if needed, so that the dough holds together and handles easily.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Tear bread; place in grocery bag and leave open overnight. Saute onions and celery in butter until soft. Wet bread with water. Squeeze water out and add to onions and celery until brown. Stuff into turkey and place remainder in pan and bake until top is crisp.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop fine or grind and cook slowly for several hours.
Add 1 cup sugar and salt to taste.
Cook a few minutes longer and put in jar.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan (greased), layer: chicken on bottom (boiled and bone out; break pieces and cover pan), broccoli (thaw and squeeze out excess water), slices of Velveeta and can of soup. Make 1 package of Stove Top stuffing; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into gallon container. Finish with enough water to make gallon.
Can add ginger ale to punch bowl if desired.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Remove any shell from crab and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs and butter.
Add crab meat to mixture and use to fill 4 or 6 scallop shells or crab ramekins (depending on size).
Top with crumbs that have been tossed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar, milk, syrup and salt; stir until dissolved.
Boil until soft ball stage, about 234°.
Remove from heat, add butter (do not stir).
Let cool until bottom is just warm.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir fast until thick.
Thickens quickly.
Put into pan.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Boil water, rhubarb and sugar 15 minutes.
Remove from burner. Add strawberry or raspberry Jell-O and stir.
Pour into sterilized jelly jars and cover with wax.

title: perfect potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes; place in colander to drain.
Place potatoes in bowl.
Beat eggs; add to potatoes with flour, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Drop potato mixture into oil by spoonfuls.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn and fry other side.
Place on paper toweling to drain.
Keep warm.
Serve with syrup or applesauce.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted margarine.
Stir in Nestle chocolate morsels and nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve as is or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate.
Bake in well-greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan (also makes good muffins).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracklin' spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
combine water and milk and heat to simmer.
Slowly add cornmeal, salt, sugar and butter or margarine.
Stir over medium heat until the mixture is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs with baking powder until very light and fluffy, then add to cornmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in cracklings.
Pour into prepared dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Add salt and water.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Stir liquids into meat mixture and bring to steaming point.
Add pineapple, green pepper and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) generously.
Beat all ingredients vigorously with spoon for 30 seconds.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Loosen side of loaf, then remove from pan.

title: mexican black bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Soak overnight in enough water to cover beans.
Discard water.
In a large Dutch oven, cover beans with 1 1/2 to 2 quarts of water.
Cook, covered, 1 hour.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 3 more hours.
Salt and pepper to taste. Let soup cool slightly.
Place in small batches in food processor. Puree until smooth.
Serve with steamed white rice or as an accompaniment with rice.
Freezes well.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Make ground beef into patties and season.
Cut onions into thick slices and spread on bottom of casserole dish under patties. Add a layer of raw sliced potatoes.
Add a layer of green peppers, sliced.
Add 1/2 head of raw cabbage, cut into fairly large pieces.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Cover entire casserole with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Do not peep.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Thinly slice flank steak, diagonally.
Brown with onion in oil.
Stir
in mixture of brown gravy mix, 1 1/4 cups water and soy
sauce.
Stir
until
thickened.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add
2 large green peppers, cut in thin strips and 1 large tomato
(if desired), cut in wedges.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve over rice.

title: pasta with fresh tomatoes
directions: Bring water to rolling boil. Add pasta; cook 5 minutes or until done. Drain. Combine tomato and remaining 8 ingredients in large bowl. Add pasta to tomato mixture and mix well. Serve at room temperature. Yields about 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie(custard)
directions: Mash
with
potato
masher,
then beat well.
Add milk. Stir until mixed well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top of pie with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard sets.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Whip butter in medium saucepan.
Add pepper, paprika, salt, rosemary, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, cayenne, garlic and water.
Put saucepan over medium heat; heat, stirring until butter mixture melts, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: batter dipped meatballs
directions: Two hours before serving, prepare Mustard Sauce.
Mix ingredients until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and wax.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin wax.
While hot, dip balls in chocolate and lay on wax paper.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put cut up chicken in soup pot.
Add vegetables and seasonings (except flour) with 3 cups liquid or enough to cover.
Bring to boil and simmer 35 minutes, until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Remove chicken and vegetables and strain broth.
Make thickening with flour; return to pan.
Bring to a boil the vegetables and chicken.
Make dumplings and cook according to directions.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Pierce broccoli package with fork. Place broccoli in microwave oven and cook on High 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly, drain and pour into serving dish.
Set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add milk, just enough to moisten, and put in a loaf pan.
Cover with soup.
Bake 40 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: creamed hamburger patties
directions: Soak bread in 1/2 cup milk and egg.
Add meat, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into patties.
Brown patties on both sides.
Put into deep casserole dish.
Add the mushroom soup and 1 can of milk.
Make a smooth sauce out of the liquids and pour over patties.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water to which a pinch of sugar has been added.
Set aside.
Combine all flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead enough to hold together.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick and cut.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: onion bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Allow to soften for 5 minutes. Stir onion soup mix into 2 cups water.
Simmer, covered, 12 minutes.
Mix in sugar, salt and shortening; cool.
Stir 2 cups flour into onion soup mix; add yeast and enough flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Knead on board sprinkled with flour and cheese until dough is smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until doubled.
Divide into two parts.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Shape into long tapered loaves.
Grease baking sheet. Coat with cornmeal.
Arrange loaves so they do not touch.
Make 1/4-inch deep diagonal slice in tops at 3-inch intervals.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Brush loaves with a mixture of egg white and water. Continue to bake 15 minutes more.
Remove; place on wire rack to cool.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple and blueberry filling. Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
