Put on topping after jello is completely set.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and pour off grease.
In a large Dutch oven, combine ingredients and cook until good and hot!
Serve with cornbread.

title: spinach and pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add drained, sliced mushrooms, spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer on sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread crescent rolls over the top.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel pecan spice loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour dressing over them.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Put in flour, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with 4x or 10x sugar while warm if desired.

title: mexican hot potatoes
directions: In large skillet brown beef with onion and garlic; drain. Stir in sour cream, salsa, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Serve over hot baked potatoes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add 1/2 package spaghetti sauce mix and tomato puree; simmer.
Cover bottom of browned pie shell with layer of meat sauce, then layer of cheese.
Alternate meat sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
Top pie with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Blend butter with sugar and flour; add egg yolks, lemon juice and peel and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 8 minutes, then in moderate oven (325°) for 25 minutes.
Like my mother used to bake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix graham crackers with margarine; press into pie pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°; cool.
Make pudding according to package directions; add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Pour into cool crust; top with whipped topping.

title: hanukah donuts
directions: You will need deep fry equipment.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 10 x 13-inch pan mix both cans of cream of celery soup with 2 cans of water.
Place chicken pieces in this mixture.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put all ingredients in a bag and shake until well mixed. Store in a sealed container.

title: apple-pineapple salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened.
Cool, then add apples and nuts.
Spread mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with cherries, if desired.

title: candy covered popcorn
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour in small amounts over popcorn.
Mix.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron frypan.
Mix the rest of the recipe in saucepan, stirring constantly over heat.
When 1/2 cup of sugar is brown, add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook until mixture will not drip off wooden spoon easily, or forms soft balls when dropped in cool water.
Remove from heat.
Beat and ice cake layers.

title: queso with a kick
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Heat Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, garlic and sausage on low until boiling, then reduce heat to simmer and add Velveeta cheese.
Stir often to avoid burning.
Once cheese is melted, stir in remaining ingredients thoroughly and pig out.

title: pig salad
directions: Put peas, uncooked and left frozen, into large bowl.
Add celery, nuts, onions and bacon bits.
Mix sour cream and Miracle Whip together and toss with salad.
Best when made 12 hours ahead. Refrigerate.

title: oyster pie
directions: Layer 1 inch soda crackers in bottom of greased casserole. Next, layer 1/2 the potatoes, 1/2 eggs, 1/2 oysters and dots of butter.
Layer again.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: caramels and chinese noodles
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter.
Add Chinese noodles to mixture.
Chop up in the melted mixture. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup warm water (from tap).
Mix softened cream cheese with gelatin.
Warm soup.
Add all of the ingredients to the soup and stir until thoroughly combined.
Melt butter (a tablespoon or so) over the entire mixture.
Refrigerate for approximately 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over a bed of lettuce with small slices of bread.

title: pass me more pickles
directions: Cook all ingredients in galvanized pan or kettle until tender and transparent.
Thicken, if desired.
Turn off heat.
Pack in jars and seal.
Do not need to process.
Just be sure jars are clean and hot.
Makes 5 to 7 quarts.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemonade, orange juice, water and lime juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and soda water. Pour over a block of ice.
Garnish with orange, lemon and lime slices, mint and strawberries.
Add vodka, if desired.

title: reindeer fodder
directions: Melt almond bark and pour over the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Will harden real quick.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put chops in bottom of a baking dish; sprinkle rice over top and then add pepper and onions.
Pour water over this; add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° covered.

title: pork chops in tomato sauce
directions: Brown pork chops and cook.
Put in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook
chicken
in salted water.
Cook, debone and chop. Cook rice according
to
package directions.
Place mixture in large casserole
dish
that
has
been
buttered.
Add
other ingredients except cheese and mix well. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: eggs stuffed with mushrooms
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove the yolks.
Drain and chop mushrooms.
Mash egg yolks.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stuff mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with chopped pimiento or sliced olives.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs with figs.
Add
flour and milk. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at
in tube pan or sheet pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onions until tender.
Mix eggs and mayonnaise with drained squash and onions.
Top with shredded cheese and then buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish.

title: schokoladeschaumden(chocolate puffs)
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Still beating, gradually add sugar and vinegar.
The mixture must remain stiff.
Add 1 tablespoon chocolate powder and 1 teaspoon cocoa to the egg white mixture. Place in little spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake it in a very slow 250° (120°C) oven for 15 to 16 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: apple pizza
directions: Make pie crust to fit pizza pan. Slice apples to cover crust (about 3).
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples (or roll apples in juice before putting on crust), then sprinkle cinnamon mixture over this.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and butter into pea size crumbles. Sprinkle over top.
A few minutes before removing from the oven, sprinkle the cheese (can cut down on cheese).
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: casserole tyson
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients into oven-going casserole and mix thoroughly.
Add fresh mushrooms last.
Cover and place in 325° oven for 3 hours.
Take to the table in casserole right from the oven.
I use this a lot on holidays.

title: spinach dip
directions: In bowl, mix sour cream, spinach, red pepper, scallions, garlic and liquid hot pepper until well blended.
Cover, chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Contains 17 calories, 32 mg. sodium and 0 grams fat per serving (1 cracker with 2 teaspoons dip).

title: maryland crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add about 5 cups water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.

title: cherry-raspberry pie
directions: Drain raspberries and cherries.
Add enough cherry and raspberry syrup to make 1 cup.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian broccoli salad
directions: Cut head of broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Add drained pineapple (save juice).
Add bacon bits and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Mix pineapple juice and mayo to make topping for salad.
Pour topping on chilled salad and toss.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together just before serving.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: To make sauce, blend soups, tomatoes and chicken broth until smooth.

In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place a layer of chicken, a layer of tortilla chips, 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the sauce. Repeat the layers, ending with the grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one pot spaghetti
directions: Combine broth, vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil, cornstarch and sugar; set aside.
In large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add shrimp; cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp just start to turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Transfer to plate with slotted spoon. Reduce heat to medium.
Add scallions, ginger and garlic to skillet.
Cook until scallions soften slightly, about 1 minute. Add peppers; cook, stirring frequently, until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in broth mixture.
Add shrimp.
Bring to simmer. Cook until sauce thickens slightly and shrimp are heated through.

title: raspberry cranberry sauce
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients and cook until cranberries pop.
Can be made in microwave.
It will take about 7 to 8 minutes.

title: honey coated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish; cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir and continue to cook for 4 minutes or until carrots are tender and crisp.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together.
Pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Cool.
Add egg.
Add bread crumbs, onions, seasonings and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together.
Cook large pasta shells.
Stuff shells with ground chuck mixture.
Put in 8 x 8 or 9 x 13 pan, depending on number of shells needed, after spreading a small amount of spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan.
Cover shells with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: *pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flavoring and flour.
Bake for 1 hour or a little longer at 325°. Grease and flour pan.
Bake either in loaf or tube pan.

title: quick-easy-good banana cake
directions: Mash bananas with baking soda in small bowl and set aside. Mix margarine, oil and sugar together.
Add and mix eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix.
Add milk and vanilla and mix. Stir in the bananas and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Don't overbake.

title: almond bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham crackers and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven and sprinkle coconut and Eagle Brand milk over the baked mixture.
Bake an additional 18 minutes.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Empty pumpkin into large mixing bowl and beat for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients beating after each one.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans covered with water and broth.
Add chopped onion, garlic and butter.
When
almost done, add green chili peppers. When done, serve in individual bowls.
Cover with grated cheese and several spoons of salsa.
May add a cup of diced chicken.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and salt. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
One-half cup chopped nuts may be added to batter before baking.

title: low cholesterol sunshine carrots
directions: Place carrots in a greased baking dish.
Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.
Add the pineapple to the carrots and mix well.
Combine the reserved juice with the brown sugar, tapioca and salt, stirring until dissolved.
Pour over the carrot mixture and dot with margarine.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
A 1/2-cup serving equals 0 mg cholesterol.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Debone and grind fine.
Add chopped ingredients.
Mix
together with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon like cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Bring Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and butter to room temperature.
Add milk, onion, pimiento and Worcestershire sauce. Beat until combined. Chill for 4 hours.
To serve, shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and egg, then add apples and vanilla. Pour into pie crust; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel, dice and boil potatoes.
Whip potatoes.
Beat in sour cream and salt.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add the onion and celery; cook until onion is transparent.
Stir in sauerkraut, noodles, soup and mushrooms; season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in 400° oven, about 5 minutes.
Stir in thyme, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 22 to 27 minutes or until vegetables are crispy tender.
Serves 6.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes. Slice evenly. Salt and pepper to taste. Place Breaded flour in a ziploc bag and add tomatoes a few at a time. Shake off excess batter and place in hot oil. Turn heat down to med-high and cook for about 6-8 minutes, turning frequently. Drain on paper towels. Enjoy!

title: ice cream pie
directions: Place ice cream in a bowl and stir until smooth. Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared cake pans (3 layers).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: bill ring cobbler
directions: Put fruit on to heat and melt butter in 8 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Prepare batter and put half into baking pan.
Pour in hot fruit and top with rest of batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until crust browns.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello, bouillon cube and Worcestershire sauce in boiling water.
Cool.
Mix the mayonnaise, onion, celery and corned beef.
Fold together.
Place in mold and chill.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry until brown, approximately 1 minute on each side.

title: mary lou britt's ice cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water; set aside to cool. Mix all together in ice cream freezer; turn until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, brown beef and cook onion, garlic and oregano until onion is tender.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
In shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch), arrange 3 alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese (optional), meat sauce and cheeses.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange delight - fat free
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip or Estee whipped topping.

title: italian shrimp(stove top)
directions: Melt margarine and mix dressing and lemon juice in skillet. Stir in shrimp.
Saute for 10 minutes, turning occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fabulous baked antarctic queen
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the ingredients in the following order:
butter, crumbs, fish, salt and pepper, lemon juice, cheese and sour cream.
Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Place paper liners in 7 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Arrange cups in circle on 12-inch plate.
Mix baking mix, milk, egg, sugar, butter and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Fill cups 1/2 full. Microwave uncovered on High 3 minutes (tops spring back when touched lightly).
Remove puffs.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Dip tops of puffs into melted butter, then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: holly berry punch
directions: Combine juices, water and grenadine and mix well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour over ice in punchbowl.
Float slices of lemon and/or orange for garnish, if desired.
Makes approximately 2-3 quarts.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Marinate for at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with toothpicks on a platter, lined with lettuce leaves.
I remove from marinade with a slotted spoon.
If shrimp are small, serve with crackers on the side.
Serves 20+.
A great make-ahead appetizer for a crowd.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown bell pepper and onion. Add hamburger and brown.
Add tomatoes with juice and corn, stir well.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour in corn meal and half can olives.
You may need to separate some and put into baking dish or you will overflow your skillet.
Pour remaining mix into baking dish.
Top with remaining olives and cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° uncovered.
Serve with French bread and salad.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In mixer, cream sugar, butter and sour cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla.
At slower speed add flour a little bit at a time.
Pour into large greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, take off bones and cut up.
Mix melted butter, both kinds of soup, chestnuts and chicken together.
Put one package of crushed crackers in a large bowl.
Pour the mixture. Add crackers on top with a little margarine.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: laffite rum punch
directions: Remove pineapple meat from shell.
Slice and dice.
Make syrup with sugar and water, boiling a few minutes; cool, then pour over pineapple.
Mix all other ingredients except strawberries and chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken creole
directions: Heat oil, add chicken and cook over medium

heat until brown. Remove chicken (keep warm). Add tomato sauce, broth, okra and hot sauce to pan. Mix well, scraping your brown bits. Return chicken to pan. Spoon sauce over chicken and cook, covered, for 20 minutes. Serve over rice or with potatoes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken and top with cheese.
Stir soup and milk together and spread over cheese. Combine margarine and stuffing.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: english pasties
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
All ingredients are raw.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease sides and bottom of 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Pour rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt over rice. Arrange salted and peppered chicken on top of rice.
Blend mushroom soup and 1 cup water.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle onion soup over top.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry-pineapple cobbler
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple.
Place mixture in pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese to mix.
Add the remainder to top.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
flour	and
milk in bowl; beat smooth. Melt butter
in	baking	dish.
Spoon half the batter into the dish. Add peaches and juice; top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and peanut butter together in large bowl in microwave.
Stir well.
Pour in cornflakes; mix.

title: pecan crackers
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and break crackers apart to place on foil.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Boil margarine, sugar and vanilla for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: croquettes
directions: Drain salmon liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough milk to equal 3/4 cup.
Set aside.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef in a skillet and drain.
Stir together beef, salt, pepper and onion; set aside.
Combine vegetables and beans in a large saucepan; cook until boiling.
Stir in meat mixture and soup.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: nanas goreng(fried pineapple)
directions: Mix flour, egg and salt in a bowl.
Dip pineapple slices in this mixture and fry in hot oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with cinnamon/sugar.

title: leslie's brisket
directions: In a roaster on top of the stove, slice 2 onions; sprinkle with salt (optional), pepper, garlic and flour.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover.
Cook on very low flame 1/2 hour.
Add meat.
Turn a few times and add another 1/2 cup water and one can tomato sauce.
Turn a few times and cook 2 hours.
Take meat out and cool.
Slice potatoes into pot.
Slice cooled meat.
Place on top of potatoes.
Cook 45 minutes more.
Add water, if necessary.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine margarine, stuffing mix and 1 cup water in bowl tossing lightly until well mixed.
Spoon half the stuffing in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, salt and mayonnaise in bowl.
Spread over dressing.
Top with remaining dressing.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over casserole. Chill covered for several hours or overnight.
Let stand 1 hour. Spread soup over top; bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven until melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: Add water to oysters and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Strain and reserve oysters and water separately; refrigerate until ready to use.

title: summer spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse and cool.
Add Italian dressing.
Add chopped green pepper, onion and chopped tomato.
Chill for a few hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except poppy seed for 2 minutes; add poppy seed and stir gently.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and cream well, using hand mixer to whip it well.
Add the remaining 4 ounces of Cool Whip for topping.
Pour in graham cracker ready crust.
This pie freezes well.

title: almond dream bars
directions: Line bottom of a buttered 8-inch square pan with 9 graham crackers.
In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat. Immediately stir in graham cracker crumbs, 3/4 cup almonds, coconut and apricots.
Reserve remaining almonds for topping.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cook cake by directions on box.
Cook in sheet pan.
Cut in squares.
Remove ice cream and cut in squares the size of cake squares.
Put the ice cream between 2 cake squares.
Heat chocolate syrup and pour over cake.
Top with cream or Cool Whip.
Add cherry for looks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix corn bread crumbs and butter together.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 400 degree for 35 minutes.

title: virginia chili
directions: Brown
beef
in
skillet.
Add
onion
and green pepper, cooking
until
onion is transparent.
Add chili powder, cumin, allspice
and
black
pepper; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Put the
remaining
ingredients in a large pan and bring to a boil. Add meat mixture;
reduce heat and simmer about 3 hours.
(Stir often or chocolate will cause it to stick.) Remove bay leaf and serve with corn bread or muffins, finely grated cheese or small cheese
crackers.
This
recipe
won first prize in State Chili contest which was held in Lynchburg, Virginia.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In oven, melt butter in baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Tilt dish to coat bottom with butter.
In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended. Stir in onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set but still moist, about 35 minutes.
Bake Oven Canadian-Style Bacon while omelet is baking.
Cut omelet into twelve 3-inch squares.
Arrange on large platter with bacon slices.
Makes 12 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine; add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three greased 9-inch pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost.
Can be baked in two layers and cut each crosswise, making four layer cake.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jell-o together. Add pineapple, pecans, marshmallows, cherries, and coconut. Mix well and fold in Cool Whip. Chill well before serving.

title: cheesy olive triangles
directions: Grate cheese; chop olives.
Mince onion and mix together.
Add mayonnaise until mixture holds together and is slightly moist. Season with pinch of cayenne pepper to taste.
Cut bread into triangles.
Spread with mixture, mounding slightly more in the middle of the triangle.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven until cheese bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: chinese barbecued baby drumsticks
directions: Separate each wing into 3 pieces.
Discard the tips.
Marinate the wings and all other ingredients, well mixed, for about 2 hours, turning if necessary, so all pieces are covered.
Bake in shallow pan, uncovered, for 1 hour or longer at 350°.
Turn once and baste 2 or 3 times.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients with an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir the frosting into the mix.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: snappy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Serve tuna salad on a bed of lettuce or between bread slices.
Makes 2 servings.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water; cool.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Add flour and buttermilk; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in 8-inch square pan over low heat on stove top.
Remove from heat and beat in sugar and eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix in.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: london broil and ziti
directions: Slice london broil in half.
Brown in salt pork drippings. Remove and cut into thick slices.
Place in pan.
Add wine and simmer.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve with Ziti.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: apple macaroon pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Slice apples in pan.
Sprinkle mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Beat eggs; add flour, sugar and butter.
Pour over apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Slice like pie.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium bowl and set aside.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Melt margarine, sugar and milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips, vanilla and nuts until melted.
Spread over crackers.

title: pumpkin bread(2 large loaves)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add and mix in sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and
soda.
Add flour mixture to first mixture, a little at a time alternately with water and vanilla.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Can glaze with powdered sugar.

title: corn flake peanut butter delight
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: ham, broccoli and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Rinse broccoli with cold water to separate. Drain.
Heat noodles, sauce mix and water to boiling.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in ham, broccoli, sour cream and onion.
Pour into ungreased oblong baking dish or 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cereal, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to boiling point.
Cut cucumbers lengthwise into narrow strips, leaving peeling on. Place in large bowl and cover with water and ice cubes.
Leave for 3 hours, adding more ice if necessary.
Drain and pack upright into jars.
Add 1 or 2 onion slices and a stalk of celery.
Cover with syrup and seal.

title: jello pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add lemon juice. Set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.

title: rum cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and beat well for five minutes.
Pour batter in greased cake pan.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over chops.
Sprinkle onion and celery over the top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and remove from bone.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix broth, milk and soup; pour over chicken.
Cook celery and onions in a small amount of margarine, until tender. Add beaten egg and dressing mix.
Spread over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy banana creme pie
directions: Slice bananas to cover bottom of pie shell in a single layer. (Kids love to do this step.)
In a medium bowl, add cream cheese and a small amount of the milk.
Blend on low speed with mixer. Alternately add pudding and milk, beating on medium speed for 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Slice banana and place on top of pie.
(Kids also like this step.) Invert pie shell lid; place on top of pie.
Store in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix altogether with 1/2 pint of sweetened cream.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
Beat the eggs (yolks too) until fluffy.
Add sugar, salt, butter and yeast water.
Add flour slowly.
If preparing rolls far in advance of a meal (a good idea with these), refrigerate dough until ready to bake.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of four, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Push chicken to the side and add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook and stir a few minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix this in a 9 x 13-inch pan with fork.
Use amount of oil, eggs and water per mix instructions.
Pour oil in bottom of pan and add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Make the cake according to package directions.
Put half into cake pan, greased and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: arkansas fudge
directions: In large skillet, add sugar, chocolate, syrup, milk and salt. Stir over
medium
heat until chocolate is melted.	May turn heat up and
cook until it reaches a rolling boil.
(Stir all this time.) Boil
minutes.
I usually turn mine down to medium-high for this
2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Allow to cool and beat
until thick.	Pour into buttered pan.
If it gets too hard, add
a
"tad"
of
milk
and
heat again.
Good luck!!!!!

title: apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In shallow dish, combine preserves, lemon juice, soy sauce and salt. Coat chicken with mixture.

Roll chicken in bread crumbs. Reserve remaining apricot mixture. Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish and drizzle with melted margarine. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes or until tender. In small saucepan, simmer remaining apricot mixture 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over chicken before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut up steak in small pieces; brown in a little grease.
Add onion, green pepper, soy sauce and mushroom soup.
Simmer until pepper is soft.
Pour over rice.

title: fluffy oven eggs and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Break up.
Add onion to bacon grease and cook.
Drain bacon and onions.
Spread bacon and mix in bottom of greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Beat Bisquick, eggs, milk, salt and pepper with hand beater until almost smooth.
Slowly pour over bacon mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Set oven to 375°.
Bake for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Cook sausage and drain well. Add cheese, which has been cut in small pieces, oregano and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Spread on bread. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
May be frozen, then cooked.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
Add beaten eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Beat until just smooth. Pour batter into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: haddock(poor man's lobster)
directions: Cut haddock in half or three pieces.
Bring to boil water with salt and onions, also bay leaf.
Cook about 5 minutes or until fish flakes.
Drain.
Pour melted butter over.
Sprinkle paprika and broil 2 minutes.
Or you can have melted butter in small cups for each person to dip.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil water; add raisins and let soak until plump.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with raisins and water.
Mix very well.

title: taco salad
directions: In heavy skillet, brown beef; drain excess fat. Add refried beans and taco seasoning. Add enough water to make like creamed potatoes. Simmer until hot, stirring constantly. Line plate with lettuce, tortilla chips, onions, tomatoes and cheese in that order. Pour taco sauce over.

title: applesauce spice bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add applesauce, shortening and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs. Beat 2 minutes more.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat eggs 10 minutes; add other stick of melted butter and powdered sugar.
Pour over graham cracker mixture.
In order given, layer bananas, drained pineapple, Cool Whip, pie filling and nuts over egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Add chopped pecans, if desired.
Pour into greased pan or Jell-O mold.

title: shrimp and crab seafood dressing
directions: Saute celery and onions in a little butter for a few minutes, until it changes color. Mix all ingredients and put into a greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-rice bake(fat-free)
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Steam zucchini until crisp-tender.
Mix all ingredients together except tomato.
Place in a 3-quart casserole and add tomato slices to top; sprinkle with fresh parsley if desired.
Cover to bake; remove cover for last 10 minutes in oven.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: apple-oatmeal crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread the sliced apples over the bottom of a greased 8x8x2 baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour and oats, then stir in the melted butter.
Spread this mixture over the apples.
Pour the water evenly over the top.
Bake, uncovered, until the apples are tender -- about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature with the whipped cream if desired.

title: greek salad
directions: In a jar, shake together oil, lemon juice, Italian dressing mix and oregano.
In salad bowl, toss together the greens, tomatoes and 1/4 cup each of the ripe olives and Feta cheese with enough dressing to coat lightly.
Garnish with remaining olives, cheese, and anchovy fillets.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix ingredients by hand, leaving lumps in avocados.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, cover the bottom of the pan with all of the chicken.
Next, layer the broccoli over the chicken. Empty the entire can of cream of mushroom soup over the broccoli. Lay the cubed Velveeta cheese on top.
Prepare the stuffing as directed on the box; do not cook.
The stuffing works as the crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: petite cheesecake
directions: Place vanilla wafers in a cupcake paper in a muffin pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour mixture over vanilla wafers; fill about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Spoon pie filling over cooled cheesecake.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix in double boiler until it peaks.

title: layered salad
directions: In flat dish, add layer of lettuce, layer of onions, layer of celery and layer of frozen garden peas.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise; put over top of other layers.
Add a layer of bacon bits and a layer of grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potatoes with topping
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix everything but phyllo and butter in a food processor. Spray an 11 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Lay 3 or 4 sheets of phyllo in pan; brush very generously with butter.
Repeat with 3 or more sheets.
Spread thin layer of spinach mixture over sheets.
Repeat until all ingredients have been used, ending with several sheets of dough, buttered as before.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Let cool a little before cutting.
If any is left over, wrap individual pieces in foil and refrigerate.
Heat in foil when needed.
Keeps a week.
